m.n: A Sign of Things to Come

de._cdata: From the stars to the gutter - a motorbike point to point corkscrewing down from the famous sign in Vinewood to the gates of Bolingbroke Penitentiary in the Grand Senora Desert.

So, now you're getting used to life at sea, how about an important lesson? Always - and I mean always - pander to the rich and powerful. I hear the Pacific Country Club might need a leg-up from someone resourceful and, preferably, amoral. You in?

Here's another tip for you, boss. Always know when to have a rest. It's the captain's privilege to take a sunny pleasure cruise from time to time so let's put our feet up and enjoy a relaxing, uneventful day. I'm sure absolutely nothing will interrupt us.

Some say charting a course is the most valuable nautical skill a captain has. But plotting revenge comes a close second, so I think it's time we develop that little talent by going after the wankers who kidnapped me.

Right, boss. If you're looking for a chance to get your feet wet in the captain's chair, it's here. Now. No pressure, obviously, but if you don't come right away there might be some serious paperwork involved...
Good news! The perfect opportunity for your next experience at the helm has just come up. How about some seaside salvage, boss? It's not stealing. You're just cleaning the ocean.

I assume you've heard of Merryweather Security? Those warmongers for hire making billions in the Middle East? Well, now they're trying to expand their domestic operations. Some associates of mine are prepared to pay top dollar for a Titan transport plane if it can be relieved from Merryweather's protection at Los Santos International. Use a helicopter to get into the airport and stay out of restricted airspace. The buyers are waiting at Sandy Shores airfield.
If you thought Sandy Shores couldn't get any shadier, try this deathmatch around Ace Liquor and the gas station. Trevor and Chef aren't cooking, thankfully.
Discover the great outdoors like your pioneer ancestors did before you, even if that means killing whoever gets in your way. Offroad point to point race through the Paleto forest with a large jump.
Get spiritual, face your fears, soil yourself...this one has it all. A jump from 7870ft that combines a rapid descent with some challenging turns.
Challenging figure of eight track through the seaside farms, fields, and other immigrant labor exploitation spots outside Paleto Bay in Northern Southern San Andreas. Lap race on dirt bikes.
The question isn't why you would want to freefall into Los Santos from 4000ft, it's why not? A descent with fast, sweeping turns to ensure that you arrive in style.
Make your own decision about the impact of global warming with this steep, winding jump over the Palmer-Taylor power station from 4120ft.
A Gang Attack at a storage depot in LSIA.

If a recruit shacks it on exercise, they don't need the added humiliation of hitching back to the landing strip. Practice landing where you took off with this flowing descent from 4300ft to McKenzie Airfield. On the way down you can admire the view, or ruminate on failure.
Any student of style will know: what comes up must go down. Drop from 4370ft, tune in to Radio Mirror Park, and pretend you're over all the bands as you twist and turn sharply down to the pond below.

Less violent than the average apartment building residents' committee meeting, this cramped LTS pits two wings of a building against each other. Try to stay on the rooftops, and look for long-ranged attacks across the courtyard and close-quarters clashes on the footbridge.
From a towering symbol of Federal control, the FIB Headquarters, to evidence of 'great' individual freedom, Ammu-Nation. Bicycle point to point through Downtown LS with some jumps.
A Gang Attack in Chamberlain Hills.
Create an artificial scarcity in the arms market at Fort Zancudo using an all-singing, all-dancing, state of the art, restored and modified classic car.
Before the drones show up and this military base is taken over by robots, use the runways to push your vehicle to its limit. Simple loop lap race for cars and motorbikes at Fort Zancudo.
Point to point motorbike race through North-Western Los Santos, starting above the city at the Kortz Center, and finishing in the heart of old downtown, Legion Square.

I've got seven trucks for you. And soon you're going to have seven burning wrecks for me, okay? Great! We'll all be happy. It's a rival operation, so shut it down, and you'll feel some of the benefit of scarcity in the marketplace.
A SecuroServ client's supply chain has been seized by police. Smash through the red tape and take back their product using a modified Big Rig.

Driving a 4x4 around Vinewood Racetrack while someone in short shorts and a monkey mask bays for your blood is the closest any of us are going to get to chariot racing in The Circus Maximus. Give the citizens their bread and games with these straight up, no-excuses laps of the horse track. No togas required.

Small town USA deathmatch in recession-hit Paleto Bay. Fight in the little used loading bays of the not so thriving shopping district. At least the funeral parlor will see some business. Works best with teams.

This dude I do some work for over at Premium Deluxe Motorsport needs a car repoed. I said you was new and in need of gainful, so thank me later for the hookup. It's a mark over on Jamestown who missed the note on a purple Schafter. This Ballas turf, you know what I'm saying, so look out and don't mention LD. Peace.

There's no shore leave to compare with the shore leave you get in Los Santos. Up to four teams of deeply frustrated mariners make landfall and create their own entertainment while the queue for the brothel dies down. Deathmatch for up to 30 players around the docklands, with a nice balance of tactical finesse and pent-up savagery.
When not cooking crank or sleeping with their sister, the O'Neil brothers set up obstacle courses... apparently. Point to point for bicycles through their ranch in Grapeseed farmland. Jumps.

Exciting news - we're expanding the TP Industries fleet with a Cargobob! All we need is you to get a hold of one from Fort Zancudo. I can lend you the plane at our airfield to get there, but you got to promise to bring it back. Oh, and you should probably take out the fighter jets so they don't come after you. R. Jakowski

Play chicken and dodge ducks with this race over Lago Zancudo. Lap course for Besra stunt jets that cuts back over itself multiple times. Expect to see wreckage in the wetlands and impact zones on the bridges.

You've spent all night stowed away in a box car eating rust and chewing your hands just to keep warm, so when the carriage stops and Los Santos embraces you with a merciless gun battle it seems like you've come home. You'll need to adapt to your new surroundings and start to think vertically if you're going to stand a chance in this brutal new world. This is going to be the start of a beautiful relationship.

What would happen if two fleets of fighter jets fell into the wrong hands? Find out as you dogfight to the death in the skies over Los Santos. Last Team Standing with 2 teams. You've only got one life, don't waste it.

There's nothing as spiritual as looking out to sea over the beauty of Raton canyon in the morning sun, weeping freely as the tear gas makes its way into your central nervous system. This is a mobile war on many fronts spread across both sides of Cassidy Creek: co-ordinate with your teammates, or risk being divided and conquered. You've only got one life, don't waste it.

Desert survival is all about setting clear priorities, and in this case food and water are less important than getting your hands on some tanks and light aircraft. Two teams aim to bury each other in the sand on this expansive LTS in the Grand Senora Desert. You'll need to use everything at your disposal to come out on top. You've only got one life, don't waste it.

Nothing ups the tension when you're dogfighting fighter jets like doing it over one of the most toxic bodies of water in the USA. Bail out at your own risk. Last Team Standing with 2 teams. You've only got one life, don't waste it.
Sun's up, surf's up, and competition for the best spots down at Vespucci beach is about to get serious.
There are so many posers in Del Perro, you need to up your game to stand out. This descent onto the beach from 4970ft with wide sweeping turns should get you noticed.
The tourists come to Vespucci for a freak show, so give them what they want with a deathmatch along the beachfront. By the time they realize it isn't pop-up performance art, it'll be too late.
Any skinny jeans wearer will know, sometimes things just don't fit. Try and squeeze up to eight compact cars around the tight corners of this lap race in Mirror Park.
One gun. One bullet. One shot. One kill. Take out an enemy to get another shot or scavenge for extra ammo. First to the target score wins.
One gun. One bullet. One shot. One kill. Take out an enemy to get another shot or scavenge for extra ammo. First to the target score wins.

With up to 30 players now tearing up the facilities at Humane Labs and Research, our sense of what constitutes a man-made ecological disaster is about to get drastically expanded. Any collateral damage in this facility will put Global Warming squarely into perspective and, as a bonus, you'll probably irradiate those hippies who've been chained to the railings for the past few months. Everyone's a winner.

There is a dealership down by Davis. They're offering reasonable finance plans, and generous repayment schedules, and encourage their customers to choose vehicles they can afford! Do you believe this? We cannot stand for it. Go over there and destroy their cars. When you come back to my showroom, I will reward you on behalf of the community.

I am not a vindictive man. The work I do is practically charity. The only thing that angers me is when people try to stop me helping. Like this club owner who takes me to court over a yellow Banshee. Please teach him a lesson, get it from his lot in Downtown Vinewood, and destroy all the other cars there. We must stand up to the bullies.

This is a disaster! Another dealership is set to open with low interest financing, and income appropriate credit limits. People living within their means makes me sick, friend, you know this. Please go to the terminal and destroy all the cars they're importing. Come back to the dealership and I will reward you for this important work. They must be stopped!

A tour of San Andreas' renewable energy infrastructure in the least green vehicles we could think of - planes. Point to point starts in Sandy Shores, dives through the windfarm, comes up over the Land Act Dam, and finishes Downtown.

Off road lap race in Pacific Bluffs. Race in a loop along the lower roads, the beachfront, and under the historic Chumash family pier. Jumps and tight turns. Avoid the rocks on the beach and through the tight gap under the pier.

What do you do with the boatyards and fishing towns on the Alamo Sea when the water's become so salinated that all the fish are dead? Use them for a deathmatch. Fight it out in the barns and boathouses of Blaine County's Galilee.

Let's face it: although you can get behind the naked aggression and anarchic mob-rule, you've never understood the rules of soccer. Well, Bomb Ball gets rid of all those fussy technicalities and restrictions on violence, and boils things down to the real heart of the matter: shoving enormous explosive devices into the other team's half before they go off. Welcome to the beautiful game.

Finish the stimulants, down your last Nogo and soda, jump a fast ride, and head for the airport to catch the red eye back home - how every Los Santos expedition ends for the seasoned business traveler. Point to point for up to 16 cars and bikes, starting on the highway and leading to smaller roads.

Well, Bomb Ball gets rid of all those fussy technicalities and restrictions on violence, and boils things down to the real heart of the matter: shoving enormous explosive devices into the other team's half before they go off. Welcome to the beautiful game.

Meth dealers are aggressive and unpredictable, especially when you arrive on their turf unannounced, and that turf happens to be a junkyard out in the Senora Desert with no witnesses for miles around. Be prepared for multiple ambushes that escalate in severity with each wave of attack.
Time for a change of regime at Fort Zancudo. Up to 30 bikers splatter their hearts and minds all over the runway. Deceptively simple lap race through an area that's restricted for a reason.

The LS canal system boasts more dead yuppy per square inch than any other water network in the country. Make some well-chosen additions to that statistic with this Deathmatch for up to 30 players that sprawls right across the glorious effluence of Vespucci.

From the sea side to mountain peaks, from hikers to technophobic, cannibalistic cultists, from state parks to secret weed farms, the San Andreas wilderness has it all. Drink it in with this lap race for choppers by Mount Chiliad and Raton Canyon.
Source a modified classic car restoration project for SecuroServ by taking the vehicle transport truck it's loaded onto. It's a rare and technologically advanced vehicle so expect armed resistance.

Alright, now our operation is underway, we need to consider our moves. Preparation is key when it comes to infiltrating the Cluckin' Bell factory, so I need you to do some groundwork. You know how to drive a train, right?

OK listen up. This mission's a good old-fashioned smash and grab. Merryweather's prepping a move, and they're taking a ton of valuable tech with them. All you gotta do is intercept. If you're lucky, you'll be in and out in no time. If you're unlucky... well let's focus on being lucky, OK?

It's duck season in this lap race for Mallard planes around South Los Santos. Fly through the thick of the smog as you buzz chimney stacks and gas guzzling freeways, and go under and between bridges in the city's soon to be outsourced industrial heart.

Like all sequels, this is more of the same with a bigger budget. Lap race for Vestra jets that weaves between buildings, and gives show-offs seven opportunities to duck under bridges. Be careful not to go down the drain when you go down the drain.
Do Loggins proud and race some fighter jets around Downtown LS and Vinewood. Weave between buildings and through construction sites on your laps. Two tight turns at either end.

Take a steep dive from 4155ft down the craggy North side of Mount Chiliad, glide in over a homeless camp to remind you why you live each minute like it's your last, then land on a spectacular beach to remind you why you live on the West Coasts.
Chopper battle over West Los Santos. Prepare for World War Three with this aerial deathmatch for Buzzard attack helicopters. Takes place over, under and around the LS River bridges.

If the years you've spent on the couch lurching from sugar coma to sugar coma have taught you anything, it's this: no deadline, no motivation. Strap a few pounds of high explosive to that deadline, give a small extension for every checkpoint you hit, throw in bonus points for random violence and an audience of millions, and your productivity is about to go through the roof.

Merryweather's ramping up of domestic operations does have a silver lining - a sudden influx of state-of-the-art military aircraft. They have two armed helicopters in storage on the Pier 400 rooftop at the west docks that would serve me very well on another job. Deliver them to the warehouse and I'll make sure you're looked after. Those psychos are tooled up so watch yourself.

m.n: By the Side of the Bay

de._cdata: Off road point to point starting in the dark heart of Mount Chiliad, shooting down its foothills, rolling through Paleto Bay, and coming to a stop on the white sands of Procopio Beach. Short road section, couple of jumps.

If your friends caught you drinking anything except a flat white at an independent coffee house it would be social suicide, but when you need java, you need java. Point to Point sedan race from Del Perro to Mirror Park passing four 'Cool Beans' coffee shops. At least it's not Bean Machine.

After this deathmatch, there'll be blood in the Vespucci canals... alongside the usual quinoa packets and cannabis prescription bottles. Fight through the alleyways, waterways, and apartment blocks of the city's most champagne-happy neighborhood.
The idyllic coast at the foot of the San Chianski mountain range won't be unspoiled by the time this deathmatch is over, as teams battle it out among the shacks and rocks along the shoreline.

There's no need to overcomplicate things: Americans have always known how to have good, old fashioned, rats-in-a-sack, murder-orgy fun. All we need to do is provide a fresh and unpredictable set of tools, roll the cameras, and get the hell out of the way. No mercy, no disqualification, no safe word.

There's no need to overcomplicate things: Americans have always known how to have good, old fashioned, rats-in-a-sack, murder-orgy fun. All we need to do is provide a fresh and unpredictable set of tools, roll the cameras, and get the hell out of the way. No mercy, no disqualification, no safe word.
There's a meeting at the Casino to discuss the buyout situation, but you're not the only ones showing up.
All bets are off as you deal with Avery Duggan for good, sending him off with a bang.
Assist the Casino & Resort's head of security with some troublemakers on the floor.
Break up the party. Rescue Tao Cheng from a possible kidnapping by bikers at a derelict Blaine County motel.
Strike back at the Duggan family by taking out their oil and gas operations. Things will get heated.
Take the Casino's management and ownership team to discuss a buyout with the Duggan Investment Trust. Be ready for a tough negotiation.
Fight your way through Casino security to get to the vault. Gain access to the vault, take everything you can, and fight your way back out with the loot, leaving a trail of destruction behind you.

Sneak into the Casino and stealthily get past or take out security until you get to the vault. Gain access to the vault, take its contents, and make your way back out of the Casino without anyone knowing you were there.
Using disguises, enter the Casino and make your way past security to the vault. Gain access to the vault, take its contents, and get out of there before they even know they've been robbed.
A Gang Attack at Catfish View.
A Gang Attack at Stoner Cement Works in Vinewood Hills.
Chamberlain Hills is so edgy even the hipsters are too scared to gentrify it. There's only one way to stimulate a housing market this sluggish: a little artificial competition.

Deathmatch for the Chamberlain Gangster Families. Fight in the roads and on the roof tops of the quiet, suburban, but not-so-safe neighborhood, Chamberlain Hills. Deathmatch that works best for teams near Franklin and Denise's house.

I've been robbed! Again! This is what happens when you try to help a community, giving credit to losers and wastrels, helping them have a taste of the American Dream and then repossessing it from under them. They took my brand new yellow Tornado and they're parading it down Grove Street. Please get it and bring it back to the showroom.

You'll work better in teams on this deathmatch around the Vanilla Unicorn Gentleman's Club. Leon, the manager, will have some questions for you if you get too friendly with the girls, but don't worry, he'll chill out soon enough.

Sometimes this line of work is not always pleasant, my friend. Those you love, those you respect, they betray you. A woman I trusted, a woman I paid generously, a woman whose hands are as dirty as mine - she is talking to the DA at the Viceroy Hotel. Silence her, and bring me a photo to prove it. And do not bring the cops to our meeting.

Our friend Ronald is getting increasingly agitated about Merryweather Security's presence in the State, and a nervous Ron gets on my tits. Why don't you go to Sandy Shores Airfield, hack into the Merryweather Network, find their outposts and then take their choppers and blow 'em all to hell. Okay? Great!
How do you get from lunch in the Vinewood Hills to your flight at Los Santos International when it's gridlock on the La Puerta Fwy? This Chopper point to point across the city will give you an idea.

Slept with a cop last night. Woke up with handcuff marks, stubble burn, and intel on a raid they're doing on one of my labs. Dunno which one, but the chopper coordinating's coming in from the North East. Ron's setup some dune buggies at a good vantage point for you. Find the cops, take 'em out, and bring any equipment they appropriated.

The stickups keep getting bigger, dog. I got knowledge on a boat loaded with brown tar these Vagos eses brought up from Mexico, so much it sitting low in the water. If you can get from them at Chumash, and bring it to my people by the bridge at Lago Zancudo, I'll have some stacks for you. Look out though, they gonna have guards on land and sea.
Chumash gang attack

The Lost have set up a brothel at an abandoned motel in the Grand Senora. We have our own operations, and I don't like to think how this one is being run. If it's not up to standards, the cops will come down on everyone. Can you go down there and take out the bikers. Bring the girl they're using to me, and we will see she's looked after.
Mount a land and sea operation to wipe out the Lost Motorcycle Club's methamphetamine operation in Blaine County with amphibious ATV's.

Any crosseyed civilian idiot can jump from 6200ft, pull their chute, and land on the blacktop at Los Santos International. But only a rag tag bastard will be able to navigate the tight, twisting turns on this course, leading down to Devin Weston's hangar. For best views of the skyline, play on a clear morning.
Bring down a smuggling operation on a Super Yacht for SecuroServ clients using an armored Technical Truck with seafaring capabilities.

Pack you some granola bars and a misplaced sense of superiority for this Last Team Standing for two teams on the side of Mount Gordo. Who hasn't wanted to push some fellow hikers off a steep cliff and into the sea?

A crew has been running a successful import-export operation along the Palomino coastline, that is about to become a lot less successful with your help. Intercept their next shipment and deliver it to the drop-off location.

Three Runners come out to play on Covenant Avenue. One of them has to make it to the Vanilla Unicorn in under 10 minutes with only one life and a selection of weapons. A gang of five Hunters chase them down on Sanchez bikes using only sawed-off shotguns. The Hunters have unlimited lives.

Three Runners come out to play at the Redwood Lights Track. One of them has to make it to the Rebel Radio building in under 10 minutes with only one life and a selection of weapons. A gang of five Hunters chase them down on Blazer quad bikes using only sawed-off shotguns. The Hunters have unlimited lives.

Water the tree of liberty with the blood of people who may or may not be patriots. Deathmatch at the anti-capitalist slash hobo camp at the foot of Mount Chiliad. We suggest teams for this fight in Dignity Village where a ditch separates two groups of outbuildings.
Each team takes a lowrider and tries to start a war between the Vagos and the Ballas.
Test your selflessness with this deathmatch at the Altruist compound in Chiliad Mountain State Wilderness. For once, nudity and wrinkles are only optional.

Alright, we're looking at a casino theft, gang involvement, big money at stake - and that's before you've even got involved. You wanna do us both a favour and find the guy responsible? Mr Faber will thank us for it.
The cartel will have an advantage over us unless we obtain the necessary weapons and gear. But this is no impulsive smash and grab. We must select our target carefully and keep our tracks covered.

You don't need to be Families, Ballas, Vagos, LSPD, or a girl scout to get involved in this deathmatch in South Central's shopping district. Fight through the alleyways and parking lots then stop for some high-quality fast food.

Everyone in Los Santos knows that public transport is a government conspiracy undermining your freedom to enjoy a 30 car pile-up with other consenting adults. Take a stand for civil liberties on this epic point to point supercar race across most of the freeways in Los Santos. Endurance is the key.
When you are standing on top of a skyscraper in mid-construction with no elevator, there's really only one way down. A technical descent from 880ft with several tight turns.

Last night a four-part shipment of barely cut, tax-free merchandise got scattered along the coastline and islets of Paleto Bay. The only thing standing between you and a lifetime supply of paranoia and self-loathing is a group of equally well informed idiots. Prepare to get your feet wet and your hands dirty.

Every native Los Santino remembers their first trip to the pier: the Ferris Wheel, the candy floss, the roller-blading acid casualties. But they might not remember two gangs butchering each other over three bags of crystal and some dirty postcards. Grab a bag, make the long run across the sand to your base, and hope this memory isn't about to become your last.

Dog walkers and surfing talent agents look out - two import operations at either end of Chumash Beach are fighting over a shipment that's landed on the pier. Any product they can get to their spot in the sand is theirs to keep.

Three packages, two teams, one town hall. Albeit the fanciest town hall in Los Santos. If you control Rockford Hills, you control the money, and you control the city, so get the packages back to your base.

Ok time to prove yourself. For reasons that don't concern you, I have an urgent need to thin out the police presence in Los Santos and I was thinking you could cause a diversion... pay some police stations a visit, cause some chaos, lead the cops on a merry dance out of town. I'll have grenades and an armored car waiting for you at the factory. Yes, that kind of chaos...

Screw insider trading, Ponzi schemes, and disguising toxic assets with derivatives, tanks are the best way to get ahead in the financial district. Every man and woman for themselves in this Rhino deathmatch, Downtown. Uses the upper and lower levels.
A Company Mobile Operations Center has been made. Get the Ops Center to safety while maintaining speed to avoid enemy missile lock.

Often the easiest way to make crime pay is to make your competitors pay for their mistakes. A rival crew has run a big shipment of product aground just east of the Wind Farm, and are bringing in a Cargobob to try to airlift it out of there. Sabotage the salvage operation and deliver the container to the drop-off.
Drop in over Pillbox Hill from 1650ft and navigate sharp turns through all the unfinished construction projects from the good old days before the economy tanked.

It looks like Trevor's been smoking more than he's selling again, 'cause we're almost outta cooking chemicals and we ain't sold much ice. The Lost got a lab in an RV that they keep moving cross-state. It should be stocked with chems, so if you bring it back to us I'll make sure you're paid. R. Jakowski

How do you feel about taking stuff from the cops? What if those cops were dirty? Really dirty? Really, really dirty? Okay, good. They've just taken some marked cash off a contact which could cause us problems. Get it back to me before the LSPD trace it to me.

Explore the Eastern wilds of San Andreas on this point to point for choppers. Go up the coast, round El Gordo Lighthouse, buzz the farms of Grapeseed, and finish in prime alien abduction territory outside Sandy Shores.

Based on the gun crime levels in Los Santos and Blaine County, you'd be forgiven for asking where they store all those bullets. See for yourself with this deathmatch by the Ammu-Nation warehouses in Cypress Flats. Works best with teams.

If it was easy, everyone would be doing it, or at least more people would survive. Advanced level lap race for Besra Jets weaving through the Ron Alternates Wind Farm. Try not to get chopped in half by a turbine blade, or collide with a rival at the crossover.

Okay, I don't have a patent, or copyright (don't understand difference between those, do you?), or an exclusive distribution contract, but ask anyone they'll tell you, I run the crank in the Alamo Sea. Really, ask 'em and if they tell you otherwise, I'll bury them to their neck in the desert. Where was this going? Oh yeah, rival dealers moving crystal, take 'em out and bring it here.
The manufacture of meth is a dangerous business. A cook site can go up in smoke at any moment when you least expect it, as this rival gang in the Senora Desert is about to find out...
The Vagos have set up a number of new meth labs around Sandy Shores. Clearly they aren't getting the message, so it's time for a less subtle approach. Take out their operations at every location.

If you think the way up to the Altruists is dangerous, try this treacherous path down from their camp. Hold onto the foothills of Mount Chiliad all the way to Cassidy Creek in Raton Canyon. Watch out for the perilous cliff-edge turns after emerging from the long tunnel leading out to the Alamo Sea. Point to point race for dirt bikes.

Okay, don't freak out but I really need your help here. One of my runners is missing, and if we don't find him, it's only a matter of time 'til I go missing too. Help me out? I wouldn't ask if I wasn't desperate.

Following the well-beaten path of many an ambulance, this short lap race takes you from South Central Los Santos, by the police station, to the Medical Center, and back out again. Suitable for all land vehicles. Helps if you have a gunshot victim on the back seat.

Every Los Santos tourist has to take a bike ride along the beach from Del Perro to Vespucci. Point to point follows the cycle path and cuts inland. Passes Muscle Sands, where men have been swapping insecurities for steroid addiction since the 1930s.
A Gang Attack in Cypress Flats.

I got an idea here at TP Inc. about synergizing our business interests - bringing day to day dealings and profitability into line. Mushroom Hank has agreed to buy motorbikes off us, so why don't you steal some off the Lost, and drop them off at his place. We screw with the bikers and make some money for once. Ideas like that is why I take crystal. R. Jakowski
Enemy agents are using the Oppressor bikes as storage devices for stolen Company data. Get hold of the bikes and deliver them to a friendly cargo plane.
A Gang Attack in Davis Quartz.
A question of precision. Take out the enemy to earn points. Finish them with a headshot, and you'll earn a bonus. First to the target score wins.
A question of precision. Take out the enemy to earn points. Finish them with a headshot, and you'll earn a bonus. First to the target score wins.

Alright, so today you gonna stick up some cats up for they stash, if you down. It's some across the lines thing between the Ballas and the Vagos at the Los Santos State Gas Company yard in Banning. Get over there, interrupt it, and get the package. Bring it back to me, I'll break off some change, we pretend like nothing happened. That's the lick. You good?

In his foolishness, an old associate of mine is preparing to testify against me. I want him gone, and I want proof of his departure - a photograph. He's barricaded in his mansion surrounded by bodyguards and police so you'll have to use your mind. Parachute in, fly or, I don't know, anything.

So, Roger's Scrapyard - you know that joint. The Ballas are conversating with some professional type dudes out that way on topic of uncut product. You gonna get hold of the package, and bringing it back to my joint. I'll break you off something, and we go about our day like nothing's gone down. Straight?

These Merryweather, they kill who they please. Life and death - the ultimate deregulation. Someone has contracted them to go after an associate of mine. He needs to get back to Mexico where there are laws against this madness. Pick him up at the airport and travel with him to the desert airfield where we have a plane waiting. There's some aid at my lockup if you need it.
Multi-level strip mall not that far from the beach. Del Perro Plaza's the perfect place to come for fast food, a restroom break, or a deathmatch. Hose down the forecourt for the next customers.

Draw a line in the sand with this Del Perro Beach LTS. Teams start at either end of the beachfront houses. They can go at each other directly or take the pedestrian bridges across the WH to pick up weapons. Dr. Friedlander isn't running his conflict resolution seminar this week.

When you're on the run from the Lost, it's probably a good idea to avoid trapping yourself at the end of a pier. But, hindsight is a wonderful thing; for now, all you can do is hope to survive long enough to learn the lesson. Be prepared for multiple ambushes that escalate in severity with each wave of attack.

The lights on the runway in the distance at Fort Zancudo will serve as a grim reminder of the importance of landing during this jump from 2570ft. A steady descent with mostly shallow turns and a couple of dives.

Because man's first instinct when he sees an area of natural beauty is to burn through it as fast as he can churning emissions into the atmosphere and leaking oil and gas into the water, here's a Seashark race through the Zancudo Wetlands. Try to avoid getting beached on the tight turns.

The Feds must have got a bump in funding, 'cause the streets are filled with surveillance trucks today. I can't operate with these a-holes s-ing on my civil liberties. Take out the trucks before I'm out of business, and I'll throw you a bone. I got some sticky bombs at my warehouse if you need them.

Great place for a tina party, emo vandalism or a deathmatch - teams are recommended for this fight in a burnt out motel in Sandy Shores. No prizes for guessing why the Alamo Sea tourist industry died out. Hint: it wasn't the recession.

Lonely at the top, lonely at the bottom...this jump starts above the clouds and ends in the desert, so lots of time for existential questions as you freefall from 7870ft, then navigate a series of tight, twisting turns.
A Gang Attack in some abandoned desert huts.
Tank exercise in the desert outside Sandy Shores. Crush cans, glass pipes, and rattle snakes as you make tracks and craters through Trevor Philips county. Vehicle deathmatch for Rhinos.
Get the heat off Lamar's back by taking out all of the Ballas OGs and Vagos shot callers making plans against him.

We got intel on a shipment of diamonds moving through Paleto Bay. Ron's been looking for some rocks to focus a Lazer he's building to shoot down alien crafts, we could also just sell 'em. Either way, they're v v important for the future of TP Inc. We'll pay well and fairly. There's a boat at the Paleto jetty you can use to get away.
See the power of stolen water and senseless irrigation at work with this long lap race. Up to sixteen land vehicles can take this track over the hills from leafy Vinewood to the arid Grand Senora.
Fight your way through Casino security to get to the vault. Gain access to the vault, take everything you can, and fight your way back out with the loot, leaving a trail of destruction behind you.
A Gang Attack at the refinery in Cypress Flats.

Do you want ice in that? Hookies Diner in North Chumash...family restaurant, local landmark, meth distribution hub. A crew of Sandy Shores dealers have been running drugs up and down Raton Canyon from Hookies for the Lost Biker gang. Chase down the couriers, and deliver the product to the drop-off for payment.

You still looking for hustles, or you too big time now? This is a big ass hustle. These professional dudes selling weight to the Vagos by the radar array in the desert. They goin' have snipers and heavy cats protecting their stuff, but it'll be worth it if you can handle it. Deal with the shooters, get the package, and bring it back to my spot.

It is critical that our entry into the Cluckin’ Bell factory goes as planned. To ensure this, we need to sabotage the cartel’s supply lines. I’ve followed a line of investigation and I believe I know how we can achieve this. Trust me, you’ll thank yourself later for being so assiduous.

This is a sad day my friend. Not only is a close friend and colleague of mine locked in a police cell, but I have reason to believe his loyalty to me is in question. If he talks, I will be uncomfortable - and I'd rather he was dead than I was uncomfortable. There's no clean way to do this. That's why I've come to you. Go to the station and take him out.

I've used Merryweather for some very sensitive work in the past, and how do they repay my loyal custom? Some undercover FIB agent offers to buy their records, and they swallow the bait. I need the meeting disrupted, the agent dead, and those filthy little mercenaries reminded of the vital importance of client confidentiality.

Do you know how hard it is to find a good translator? One with a solid grasp of every regional dialect in South America and a strong stomach? And then before you can say ''extraordinary rendition'' the IAA stick him on a plane to their favorite black site. Well, I don't want any loose ends. Get to the airport, terminate him, and don't lead the cops back to me.

I always liked you and your crew. You're either very loyal, or very afraid. Either way, you wouldn't go behind my back with my closest associates and try to cut me out - and if you did, you're smart enough to know what I'd do to you. Well it turns out another crew of mine is not so loyal, and not so smart. I need you to educate them. And make it public - I only want to have to do this once.

You know what I hate even more than losing hard working dirty cops to IAD entrapment? Losing them on a bust so obvious my nephew wouldn't fall for it. They're being transferred between protection sites today, so this is my only chance to get between them and a plea bargain. This isn't personal or pleasure, so just make it quick.

Like a trucker, hit the blacktop and keep going 'til you run outta gas. Land vehicle point to point that loops through the Port of LS and gets on the freeway all the way to the San Chianski Mountains.

Is there anybody I hate more than Merryweather's CEO Don Percival? Ok, quite a few people. But he's enough of a snake to antagonize just for the hell of it. Merryweather are smuggling in some high-tech weapons. They're currently stashed under a bridge in a shipping container so you'll need a heavy-lift heli. See if you can borrow one from the army base?
Ey, partner, after all our chasing, looks like we know who's this beat leak shit. This is the hook, homie. Our time to shine. Go show this punk how we hussle in this business.
Take your baby for a drive with this lap race for cars and bikes around glamorous Vinewood studios, romantic Vespucci Canals, and glitzy Rockford Hills mansions. But remember, baby likes a winner.

You need a car if you're visiting Los Santos, and you need somewhere to park it when you're not sat stationary in a traffic jam. Race through two parking lots in this simple lap track for compact cars or motorbikes in Little Seoul.
Iconic or a cliche - pick up some speed as you race down the dry concrete channel of the LS River. Simple loop laps for land vehicles with two left-hand hairpin turns.

Deathmatch in the sloping backyards, parking lots, and loading bays between Spanish Ave and Vinewood Blvd in Downtown Vinewood. No matter how many participants get shot, the leading cause of death here will still be overdose.

The one downside of a drag race on the Great Ocean Highway is the crowd of concerned citizens throwing insults from the overpass. But here’s the thing: If you nail that nitrous and hit those shifts, those guys will be throwing their tighty whities instead.

With nothing standing between you and a clear run down Hawick’s main drag, it’s time to slam on the gas and kick up smoke. Not only is the burnout vital for cleaning your rear tires and providing grip, it also obscures the evidence of the multiple vehicular assaults you committed on the way here.
A Gang Attack at the scrapyard in El Burro Heights.

You can launch well, you can shift perfectly, you can time your nitrous down to a hundredth of a second, you can be the best drag racer Sandy Shores has ever seen. But the real reward? It’s the friends you write off along the way.
There are three secrets to becoming a drag race legend in San Andreas. 1) Lightning reflexes. 2) Unwavering nerves. 3) Strong cervical vertebrae. On the manic Senora Freeway, you’ll need them all.

Drag racing is technically illegal in the state of San Andreas. But don’t worry, the team’s prepared. They’ve disconnected all the cameras and bribed the local cops, so unless you’re thirst trapping on Snapmatic at 150mph, no one’s gonna know…

Want to make it to that finish line? Then you better stick your shifts and pray the G’s wipe you out at just the right moment, because nobody wants to be conscious for the smell of Clucking Bell Farms at 140mph.

m.n: Drift Race - A Hill To Die On

de._cdata: According to the celebs on Bleeter, life in Vinewood Hills brings its own unique struggles: BBLs are sagging, next door’s hot pool boy is piling on the pounds, and someone just crashed a ZR350 into the outdoor champagne fridge. It’s a hard life. Point to point race for drift vehicles.

Think of those tech bros on their beachfront balconies, watching the sunset with a chilled Cazafortunas in one hand and BAWSAQ in the other. Wouldn’t it be a shame if someone were to drift the backend of an FR36 through their portfolio..? Lap race for drift vehicles.

When the organizers say this race goes from high to low, they definitely mean the track goes from the Galileo Observatory to Downtown Vinewood. If you think they're implying that you'll hit that first precision drift, burst into flames, and barrel roll into the canyon, you're being paranoid. See you on the highlight reel. Point to point race for drift vehicles.

LSPD stats suggest gang-related deaths in Rancho have dropped in recent weeks. Perhaps it's undeniable proof that, whether you're team Vagos or team Aztecas, none of it matters behind the wheel. Or maybe it's because the local track skirts the Medical Center so drivers can patch up their stab wounds. Just do yourself a favor, avoid eye contact at the starting line. Lap race for drift vehicles.

m.n: Drift Race - Go with the Flow

de._cdata: During last year's race season, the local HOA sent a record-breaking number of complaints to the mayor of Paleto Bay. This year, the race organizers are aiming to go even higher. Drop that dirt, ride that wall, fill your lungs with toxic burnout. If they're gonna write 1000 words with caps lock on, you better give them something to write about. Lap race for drift vehicles.

What do you get if you smash La Mesa's highway, a can of neon paint, and a deranged mob of juiced-up, burnt-out drifters together? The ultimate city racetrack. And an eight-car pileup. But mostly, the ultimate city racetrack. Lap race for drift vehicles.

LSIA maintain their runway asphalt meets the latest regulatory standards, citing appropriate texture and grooving for steadfast grip. So how would you like to be the case study in their next lawsuit? Lap race for drift vehicles.

New installations, cheering crowds, fresh street art and late-night shows. Textile City's "cultural boom" sounds so good on paper. But then, the PR material conveniently leaves out the stream of drift addicts tearing up the bus center. Lap race for drift vehicles.

The port of Los Santos is the perfect setting to burn and slide into drifting godhood, so don't worry about breaking and entering. Do the docks have nightshift security workers? Yes they do. Are they all shotgunning beers at the finish line? Yes they are. Lap race for drift vehicles.
Much better use of a golf course than actually playing golf or talking about how much money you have. Race caddies around the links in this lap race and watch out for the water hazard.

The contractors who built Fort Zancudo figured that radar coverage beginning at 300ft would be more than sufficient. Prove them wrong with this twisting descent that sets you up for a freefall right into the heart of the base. Don't even think of pulling your second chute until you're inches from the tarmac.

They don't know how it started, maybe two girls got the same tattoo, or reposted a snapmatic without acknowledging it. What they do know is sides have been chosen, and East Vinewood's gone to hell. Two team LTS in both wide open spaces and close quarters.
A gang attack in East Vinewood.

I thought the ''journalists'' in Los Santos had more important agendas, like keeping celebrity out of rehab and actors in the closet. How my humble interests interest them, I don't know. Help me quieten down the editor of the Daily Globe before he shares his exclusive with the LSPD in La Mesa. And bring me his photos.

The market's about to be flooded with inferior product. I... WE... have too much invested in it to let that happen. I need you to get in some Lazer fighter jets and take out the planes holding product before they land. It sounds extreme, but these are desperate times.

High speed figure of eight laps through scuzzy Downtown and Industrial East Los Santos. Up to 30 cars - defaulting to Sports Class, because the type of person who drives one likes to speed past the disadvantaged, usually spitting out the window.

Deathmatch on Marabunte Grande territory in El Burro Heights. We recommend teams for this fight in the back yards and on the winding sloped road overlooking Los Santos. For an authentic experience, get gothic script tattooed on your face.

These Hispanic gangsters, always strutting. Have you noticed this? I gave a man from El Burro Heights credit for a manly car, an orange Dominator, but his credit history is anything but manly, so I feel we should take it back. This is gang territory, but you are tough yes? You can handle this? Good.
A SecuroServ client needs some technology in the hands of a Merryweather client. Take an armored RV to The Palmer Taylor Power Station and get it for them. They will be expecting you.
SecuroServ are on standby to extract some clients from a difficult situation. Collect modified buggies and get ready to clear their escape route for them.
Protect the nation's important allies/customers as they try to depart LSIA by private plane and helicopter. Turreted Trailers will be provided for the purpose, and should be returned.

An old, old friend was arrested in Mexico a few weeks ago. Before we could do anything to help he was extradited to the States, and now they're holding him at Fort Zancudo Military Base. It's too late to save him, so we have to green light. I would expect the same. Military resistance will be enormous, but if you take him out, so will the reward.

Be a patriot. Buy American, steal foreign. A rival crew has a fleet of top-end motorbikes at the Maibatsu factory earmarked for an upcoming job. Sabotage their plans and make some money in the process by stealing the bikes and delivering them to the drop-off. The factory is heavily guarded so make sure you scope it out before moving in.

Time to interrupt Merryweather's anti-smuggler operations. Think of it as legitimate asset acquisition, with some illegitimate steps. Merryweather don't do things by the book, so why should we? We get supplies. They get pissed off. That's a win-win for the LSA.

Ask around and you'll find that the O'Neils produce the finest crop of slow, local, organic methamphetamine in any direction. You'll also discover that when the brothers aren't skirting laws concerning acts of bestiality, they're hosting the filthiest Deathmatches in Blaine County. Up to 30 players dart between farm buildings or chance the open ground: Either way, the losers end up as fertilizer.
So, you rocked up uninvited to a secluded farmhouse in the middle of Blaine County. What did you think was going to happen?

Where Los Santos meets the old West - race off roaders through oil fields and junk yards in this lap circuit. Only a matter of time until this area is turned into shopping malls, or hipster hangouts, so enjoy it while you can. Great views.
Government contract to combat a large-scale multi-source hack on government data. Use rocket powered Voltics to get close to enemy agents and wipe their hard drives.

A'ight, so you wanna hustle? This your hustle - the Lost and the Vagos is having a meeting of minds down in the LS River. It'd suit my purposes if they got stuck up. Light 'em up, bring whatever they holding to the crib, you gonna make some bills. Straight up.

Catch the red eye with this night flight over South Los Santos. Lap race for Vestras that starts by the Maze Bank Arena, ducks under bridges, loops around Los Santos International, and returns over the tallest skyscrapers in Downtown.

m.n: First Dose 1 - Welcome to the Troupe

de._cdata: Hey, Ron here. I'm heading up to Liquor Ace. There's some kinda new crew in town. Could be trouble. I'm not saying I need your back up or anything, but... I kinda need your backup. See you up there?

OK, I got a small job for a big brain. Need someone to pick up some party supplies. Think you can handle it? Heard there's a bunch of tricycle pushers on our new turf though so let's cut the love thy neighbor crap. Don't take any shit if they get up in your face.

So, those plans you sent left me with some real deep inspiration. I mean, I'm talking a serious strategy hard-on. We're gonna hit those peddlers where it hurts. Smack em right in the distribution. BUDONKADONK!!
Newsflash, FM! You're one of us now. It's time you became a certified, bona fide Fooligan. Get down here for your initiation.

m.n: First Dose 5 - Make War not Love

de._cdata: So, now you've sampled the product, it's time to kick production up a gear. And that means flushing the market of any and all inferior products. From now on, our acid is going to be the only trip in town. Head over here when you're ready to get your hands dirty dealing with the competition.

Hey, Freshmeatloaf. You know much about Humane Labs? I heard they got some uncut science in there. You know, the could-be-cure, could-be-super-virus kinda science. Labrat says that if we're going to get this revolution started, we need a slice of that pie. Go grab your periodical table, professor. We're going in.

Two teams, two flags, one objective: what's yours is mine, what's mine stays mine. The classic capture the flag formula reworked Arena War style to include enough gasoline-chugging violence to appeal to a mainstream audience.

Like every other pilot in LS, you know you can fly a commercial jet under suspension bridges and round Ferris Wheels - now see if you can get your passengers to share your confidence. Drop the oxygen masks and take in the views with this point to point race over some of the most beautiful parts of the state.
Infiltrate a Vagos funeral, take out the gangsters, and take their package.

Push your aerobatic stunt jet to its limits with this tricky lap race around the city. You'll duck under bridges, skim the canals, trench run the LS River, and maybe, just maybe, learn something about yourself.

When your plane goes down in the backwoods of rural San Andreas, you need to address the basics to survive. Food and water. Shelter before nightfall. And a lot of guns before the kill squad on your tail catches up with you...
Fighter jet battle over Fort Zancudo Military Base in Blaine County. Military exercise or just an exercise in friendly fire. Aerial deathmatch for Lazers.

Drop whatever you're doing. I've been surveilling two trailers of weapons in Cypress Flats for a while now but they just got hit. I don't know who the crew is but they came in numbers. Get down there and stop this happening. This is my job not theirs. Deal with them and bring the trailers back to the warehouse.

A mansion in Vinewood Hills may not compensate for your early-onset hair loss and appalling children, but it makes a great playground for this intricate Deathmatch. Up to 30 players, defaulting into 4 teams, wreak havoc among the driveways and cherub fountains of the elite. Aim to get a body in every swimming pool by close of business.
Lap race for dirt bikes going up and down the Blaine County side of the Vinewood Hills. Features road and off road sections, and a large jump.

Like every other great American industry, it's only a matter of time before organised crime is outsourced to China, too. Celebrate home-grown violence while you still can with this two team LTS around the old factory sector of La Mesa. Whichever team controls the choke points and rooftops has the advantage. You've only got one life, don't waste it.
It's simple. Kill the enemy, and stop them from wiping out your team to gain points. But here's the thing: Killing your own teammates awards you a bonus. First team to reach the target score wins.

Nothing helps soothe the body and calm the nerves after air travel like a dip in the ocean, unless you hit it at 124 mph. Descent from a helicopter at 4410ft above LS International featuring tight turns and a landing on Vespucci Beach.

You may or may not know, but TP Conglomerate owns that gas station out by Ace Liquor. It don't get used much, but if there's an opportunity to fill the pumps on the cheap we take it. The Lost have a tanker of fuel at a depot near Harmony, Trevor wants you to steal it and bring it here. R. Jakowski

When it comes to brutal arena designs, you can install the most exquisitely hazardous death traps on the market, but there's just no substitute for the sheer ingenuity and sadism of a properly incentivized human being. One team collects checkpoints, the other uses every fiendish tool at the arena's disposal to make their plans go up in smoke. And be sure to hold onto your grudges: after every round, you switch places.

A'ight, word is the Vagos got a new connect for the cocaine they bringing cross border. These some professional dudes who can distribute weight, so you know we wanna screw that up. First exchange is happening at the Los Santos State Gas Company in Cypress Flats. Take 'em out and bring the package round my spot.
Sometimes you have to dig a little deeper for those sweet dopamines, and this jump delivers. A rapid descent from 5970ft, leading through tight turns and tree tops.

I am a good man, yes? I provide a valuable service to the poor and weak in this city? I give credit to the needy, and hope to the hopeless. To carry on this important noble work I need more cars. I cannot afford to buy them, but there are rich fools at Gentry Manor who can be robbed for the greater good. Please bring some of their deluxe cars back to the showroom for me.

Lots of plastic surgery? More 70s Vinewood than 50s? Measure of authenticity is how many celebrities have died in the place? Then this is the deathmatch for you. Fight between the bungalows and around the pool of Gentry Manor just off Eclipse. Works best with teams.

Rather than looking around and silently judging fellow guests at your country club, you can act out your bloodiest fantasies on them. Deathmatch that works best with teams at this exclusive members only joint on the beach in Pacific Bluffs.

When Glass Heroes got their latest shipment of 60s carburetors, they expected scalpers, but not wave after wave of heavily armed fanatics shooting their way to the front of the line. It's amazing what classic car enthusiasts will go through for some original oiled wrapping.
Motorbike race starting in the narrow canyon roads of chichi Rockford Hills, and ending in wide boulevards of scuzzy Downtown Vinewood. Point to point with an opportunity to take flight.

Eh, I got another gas tanker lick and I'm bringing it to your ass. They going to be traveling down the GOH, the buyer's already lined up and everything. There's a rumor a crew of freelancers took a contract to protect it, but we don't truck with no rumors, dog. Get the tanker and drop it at the spot in El Burro. Peace.
Point to point for boats starting in the LS River, and taking you to the Palomino Highlands on the East Coast. Hugs the coastline, but features some turns and opportunities to jump rocks and islets.
Become one with nature as you plummet through the Mount Chiliad Gorge from 3100ft, and pray that a gust of wind doesn't make you become one with the rock face.

I know what you gonna say - 'what's Martin Madrazo care about a shipment of TVs?' Martin Madrazo don't care about flatscreens, but he does care about respect, and this shipment the Ballas are moving shows clear lack of it. Take it down in Rancho, bring it to me, AND DON'T ASK ANY MORE QUESTIONS.
For a long time this place was nothing but stray dogs and trailer parks, but throw in a few oil derricks and suddenly the real estate speculation gets pretty intense.

USA! USA! USA! Only one side can win this desert Last Team Standing, but if you back America you're sure to pick the winner. Head for the rocks if you want to put on a good fireworks display, and try not to get caught out in the unforgiving open.
They're no strangers to shootouts at Grapeseed Farm; after all, their main crop is methamphetamine. Last Team Standing with 2 teams. You've got one life, don't waste it.

Sequel to smash hit Grass Route, this off road point to point starts on the North bank of the Zancudo River, passes through the wetlands, and finishes on the beach in North Chumash. Expect some of the same dirt road hijinks you enjoyed the first time around.

Starting in the Puerto Del Sol, go around the whole of beachside West Los Santos in this lap race for choppers. Aerial views of the Vespucci Canals, Richards Majestic Studios, Del Perro, and the Great Ocean Highway.

Lap race passing Los Santos International, the Maze Bank arena, and Little Seoul. You'll see lots of unused grassland where you might be able to bury a body. Cars and motorbikes. The 'Prepare to Take Off' billboard will separate the women from the girls.

Probably the best thing to do out here after tripping on peyote or snake venom. Deathmatch that works best with teams making use of big boulders, Joshua trees, and narrow dirt tracks of the Senora National Park. Should keep the vultures happy.
Welcome to the neighborhood. If you can survive here, it'll make everywhere else look like a playground...

Quick, quick, I need your help. These idiots emailed me a list of cars, and where they're parked. It's the mother lode! Top drawer premium stuff! Get them all before they figure out what happened, and I'll pay you a fraction of what they're worth. The boat will be leaving soon so hurry!

A team of pilots has to run four stunt jets from LSIA to Fort Zancudo while another team is coming in the opposite direction. Start in your rivals' hangar and use a limited supply of Buzzard attack choppers and Lazer jets to mount a defense... attack is, of course, the best form of defense.

A tractor shortage in Grapeseed leads to farmyard chaos. It's harvest time, and two rival gangs compete to bring a Fieldmaster tractor back to their bases. Farming is a deadly serious business in Blaine County.

After twelve hours 'rolling' at your local post-industrial techno-house night, your tattooed friends will be too wide-eyed to drive themselves. Pick up some taxis for them in this ultra-exclusive two team GTA style Capture based round the Downtown Cab Co depot in East Vinewood.

Like many Americans, you bought an RV only to discover that you hate being close to nature and your family. Luckily, it doubles as a mobile weed silo, and there's a bunch of hillbillies who need your services. One team gets to transport four tons of bespoke plant life from Braddock Farm to a local scrapyard, while the other team tries to intercept it and make it their own. First team with three vans back at base gets to start a traditional Blaine County Bonfire.

Rain, sleet or shine, three teams of hoods try to get their hands on some very important letters in two postal trucks at the Post Op Depository on Elysian Island. If they get a van to their spot, it's theirs.

Substance abuse might have shrunk their brains, but it won't shrink their trucks. Two bands of petrol-chugging mutants try and leave each other in the dust to get to a spare Sandking XL on the shores of the Alamo Sea. First team to get three trucks back to the ranch wins... just think how much good, honest road-kill you could stash in the back of one of those.

It's a buyer's market as rival groups attempt to deliver Buckingham military jets to LSIA. They're vintage collectors' items and they fly like that, so use Lazers for defence and attack. Each team will only have one Buckingham in play at any time. Start points are Fort Zancudo and Sandy Shores Airfield.
Parachute jump for beginners. Starts at 4130ft, takes in views of the Land Act Dam and lands between a gun shop and gas station. Kind of perfect.
It's time to make your move. Infiltrate the compound, grab the goods, and get out in one piece. How you pull this heist off is up to you.

The FIB is using a lockup on Las Lagunas Blvd to store some prototype vehicles equipped with new tech to siphon private data from home wifi networks (copied from Eyefind cars). They're watching us, I'm watching them. Can you pay them a visit and snatch their new toys? Word of warning - you'll have to hack the terminal to get into the lockup which is going to raise some bells. Expect a lot of heat.
Infiltrate enemy agent base of ops and limit their power by securing a Weaponized Half-track from their fleet. Vehicle to be returned to friendlies.
Give air traffic control a wake-up call with this rapid descent into Los Santos International Airport. Freefall from 3950ft, and try to avoid a crash landing.

I need you to shut down an import operation based out of Port City. They're all over the shipyard, so take them out there, and look for their stash in one of the offices. Once you got it, you can use their smuggling boats to bring the product to my people up the coast. And then you'll be paid.

I've got some competition based at a construction site in La Puerta. If the head of the crew had an accident, maybe they won't be so competitive, you get me? Go to the site, clap the dude, I'll make it worth your while.
Make your feelings known by carving a love heart into the Grand Senora Desert. Hills and jumps in this mainly off road lap race for bikes on a heart-shaped track.

Stick to the waterways in this chopper lap race around Los Santos. Follow the concrete river channels and fly under the bridges as you try to beat other birds from Downtown up to El Burro Heights and back to Little Seoul.

Judging from the yellow dense smog and the talking fish in the harbor, Humane Labs and Research stopped making perfume a long time ago. If you run out of ammo on this cramped LTS for two teams, you can always hurl the nearest bucket of toxic sludge at your opponents. You've only got one life, so don't waste it, or they'll use your corpse to test nerve agents.

Say what you like about gladiatorial fights to the death as a form of mass entertainment - they've got no hangups about being fair. One team takes to the arena in monster trucks capable of crushing metal and bone into the same bloody dust. The other guys get compact cars and a dose of anxiety meds - but if even one of them survives, they win. Let the games begin.

A wise man once said that to really appreciate the beauty of Los Santos you need to be plummeting towards it from 7000ft in the middle of the night. Prove him right with a fast, complex parachute jump that gives you an unparalleled view of the city lights and leaves you exhausted and defenceless on a street corner in downtown Burton.

I need another favor. Some documents are about to change hands that would be very useful to me. Security system plans - seems we both have eyes on the same prize. The exchange has been set up at a construction site on top of a skyscraper in Downtown so you'll need a helicopter. Bring the briefcase to the warehouse. Make this happen and I won't forget it.

Ight, partner. We tracked the phone and hustled the lawyer. And now? Looks like we got an invitation to the party. But this aint your average trust fund baby social. Security's gonna be tight so be cool, suss the situation, then snatch the music off that silicon asshole.
A Gang Attack at the construction yard in Rockford Hills.
A Gang Attack at a farm house in Vinewood Hills.
A Gang Attack at a hideout in the hills.

Breaking into the Cluckin’ Bell factory is one challenge, but getting out is a whole other conundrum. The bottom line is, we need a getaway vehicle, unconnected and untraceable. I trust you to make the right choice.

I got something I need help with - a list of Ballas got to get clapped. You take out these dudes in the order I give you, they ain't going to get wise to it. Any deviation, the thing is blown. It's Big T, Little T, Small F and Terrance. Get to it, you goin' get paid.

Two stickup crews compete for the rights to a Marabunta Grande convoy moving product through Banham Canyon. Whoever can rob the stationary gangsters, get the packages to their evac zone, and protect them there, will win the day.

Two importers fight over rights to a shipment at the Terminal. Scrappy close quarters battle as they try to get as much product to their side of the containers as they can, and protect it when it gets there.

A casting call gone wrong has escalated into full-blown war in the Vinewood Hills. Two troops of armed actors go full method and try to take their rivals down in their own rehearsal rooms. There are two bags of cash up for grabs, yours and your opponents', the first troop to hold both gets the part.

Every jumper's got to learn to use their back up chute. Either they learn or they go splat with the secondary still packed. Jump from 7874ft, drift down towards the Maze Bank Tower, release your primary chute, free-fall, pull the back up, and land on top of Ammu-Nation in Strawberry.

Why can none of my men look after themselves? A chief lieutenant can't even leave his house without being shot to hell by random thugs. I sent some men to try and protect him, but now they're not even answering their cells. Go to the apartment, collect the imbecile, and bring him safely back to my place.
Beat the rush hour traffic from workplace yuppie central to... residential yuppie central. Point to point starting outside Maze Bank and finishing in the Vinewood Hills.
Dirt bike race through the O'Neil Ranch in rural Grapeseed. Quick and dirty just like the crank cooked there. Short laps and a jump.

Life isn't about holding onto good things, it's about passing them on. Like inherited wealth, or a sense of entitlement. Or a high-explosive device. In Hot Bomb, one player has the bomb, and the only way to get rid of it is by crashing into someone else. Throw in a timer and a baying crowd, and survival of the fittest just got an upgrade.

An easy proposition: you get five minutes to rack up the highest score you can by taking out the enemy. The catch? The weapon in your hands will keep on changing. Transferable skills have never been so important.

Enjoy panoramic views that start off stunning and steadily deteriorate until you land at a power plant on the side of a freeway. A 2740ft jump that dives steeply over the hydro-electric station.

Some tight turns in this off-roader lap race in the Grand Senora Desert. You'll go over dirt roads, narrow paths, paved sections, and jumps as you pass the Redwood Lights Track and the Rebel Radio radio tower.
Starting on Grove Street and heading out of the city, you'll go through Ballas, Families, and Vagos turf in South Los Santos. Point to point for cars or motorbikes.

Hold onto your lunch or you'll need windshield wipers on the inside of your cockpit. Point to point for jets through the docks and Downtown. Obstacles to avoid and two loop the loops will keep you on your toes... or your head.
From Vespucci Beach to Chumash, tour some of Los Santos' stretches of coastline with this sixteen rider dirt bike point to point. Starts at the Pipeline Inn and goes inland.

A heavily guarded industrial plant out in the middle of nowhere? Clearly they're manufacturing more than just cement here, and don't take kindly to surprise guests. Be prepared for multiple ambushes that escalate in severity with each wave of attack.

Two teams increase this city's feverish reliance on speculative finance by demolishing swathes of the industrial zone. Explosive-heavy Deathmatch amid the factories and steelyards of La Mesa. You never know, if you do enough damage the craters and bullet holes will give the place just enough authenticity for a hipster revivial a few months down the line.
Take a path down the North face of the Vinewood Hills going from the Gallileo Observatory to the Redwood Lights Motocross Track. Point to point motorbike race with off road and paved sections.

I have been robbed my friend! Robbed! Me - a pillar of the community! A friend to the friendless, creditor to the creditless! They took a blue Jackal and a beautiful yellow Coquette from our garage at the docks. Go and get them back for me! I am feeling faint and must lie down.
Rescue Gerald from police custody before he's airlifted out of state.

Long point to point race for Lazers. Fighter jets will start at Fort Zancudo and go over the wetlands before coming over the Vinewood Hills rounding Downtown and finishing above Del Perro. Pilots have to go between buildings and under bridges at high speed.

Scenic tour of the outskirts of Los Santos... in fighter jets. This long point to point for Lazers takes you past some postcard-worthy landmarks. If you look hard enough, you can make out the tourists taking selfies.
Help students swap their college debt for medical bills in this lap race starting on the ULSA campus. Track covers the wide roads and narrow canyon drives of Rockford Hills. For cars and motorbikes.
Negotiate waves and small islands at this prime surf spot with no surfers. Maybe it's the sharks. Lap race for boats off Paleto Cove.

It takes a certain level of self-belief to jump out of a helicopter from 7870ft. This extremely challenging descent, with a series of tight dives, is guaranteed to satisfy your desperate need for exhibitionism.
Treat the Kortz Center museum to some performance art that truly captures the conflict of the human condition for once. Last Team Standing with 2 teams. You've only got one life, don't waste it.

At last, let your art history degree shine bright. During a skirmish in the museum gardens, you can impress your teammates with witty quips on the inherent violence of structural norms while you empty a semi-auto into the other guy's face. They'll love it.

At first you'll think it's the altitude making your eyes and nose water, but you'll soon realize that it's whatever you're breathing in from the Alamo Sea below. A literally mind-blowing descent from 3950ft with banking turns.

Trevor don't like cocaine, and he likes folks other than himself making money off it even less. These corporate dealer types are using Sandy Shores Airfield to move white cross country. Can you get hold of the planes, and take 'em to the docks. It'll be difficult to land, so get someone on the ground to guide you in. R. Jakowski

Some business associates of mine have come to me with a little market saturation problem. I need you to extract a plane loaded with rival product and deliver it to Sandy Shores Airfield. I'd advise taking along a sniper if I were you. Convince me you're professional and I'll have more jobs like this. Oh, and get an apartment, something with space to prep properly. I don't like mistakes.

I just eavesdropped on a very interesting conversation. That diamond store that got hit last week? The ice is in a helicopter in a rooftop in Del Perro ready to be moved out to the East Coast. They'll have muscle so you'd better tag-team this - put someone on a nearby roof with firepower while the other moves in for the cargo. I wouldn't normally poach, but this crew are idiots ;) Meet me back at the warehouse.
