The best training exercises are the ones that kill the most recruits. Get to grips with your backup chute, or find out if water really is as hard as concrete when you hit it at terminal velocity. Two chute jump from 6120ft over the Alamo Sea.
Emergency services are on standby for collisions at this figure of eight track on the runways of Los Santos International Airport. Lap race for four or two wheel vehicles.
Lonely truckers and enterprising hitchhikers are in for a scare as this pit stop on the Palomino sees its share of the action. Small scale LTS that'll make good use of the Heavy Shotgun.

Don't ask me how I know but Merryweather are holding some seriously hush-hush tech at the docks. Some kind of electromagnetic weapon about to be shipped out to someone dangerous. We can't let that happen. The device is in a trailer so you'll need a truck to move it. Check one of the industrial areas nearby. Good luck. They've got a lot of men on this so go prepared.
Deathmatch in Downtown Port City. Fight between highrise container stacks and under gantry cranes in the Los Santos Docks. The only activity in this part of town you don't need a union card for.

Get into Humane Labs, and get out with their files. After the EMP is triggered, half the team goes in with night vision, the other half holds off reinforcements in the attack chopper. Then the chopper team collects the ground team.

You got the explosives and the signal jammers. Sounds like we ready to rob a motherfuckin bank. Time for some old school cash grabbin, yall. Six banks. Six racks of crisp marked bills. Get em back to me and K, and we'll make sure you get some real ones.
Launch an operation on a foreign submarine lurking off the coast. One team boards through an airlock and disables the sub, while the other holds off enemy agents in an aircraft above.
It's time to make your move. Infiltrate the compound, grab the goods, and get out in one piece. How you pull this heist off is up to you.

Your alarm should have gone off hours ago, your mouth tastes like a donkey pissed in it (because one did), and you've got a marketing presentation in ten minutes - point to point from the suburbs to the city for cars and bikes.

Enjoy the stunning vistas as you rapidly descend towards Paleto Cove by Mount Chiliad... but not so much that you forget to open your chute. Long free fall from 7500ft followed by weaving and diving between checkpoints and the drop zone.
Challenging dirt bike point to point. Hold it together on this steep descent from the top of the Land Act Dam to the basin of the LS River in East Los Santos.
Rush to an IAA base under the Satellite Relay Station in the desert. Foreign agents are attacking and trying to hack government servers - they need to be stopped.

Ok. You got the transponder, you got the backup. Only question is: you ready to penetrate some crazyass nuclear bunker? We need them hard drives baby so get on it. And make sure the client comes back in one piece or your ass gonna hear it for real.
A Missile Launch Base has fallen into the wrong hands. Storm the base, clear it out, stop the warhead from launching, and save the day.
A Missile Launch Base has fallen into the wrong hands. Storm the base, clear it out, stop the warhead from launching, and save the day.

Since you got the cutting saw and that schedule, it's time to go grab them ECUs. Stop that train and get on board wit whatever moves you got. Freights en route. That's French for you better move yo ass if you wanna catch that ride, boo.
Today we worship a false god, the dollar. Spare a thought for simpler times as up to sixteen of you speed past the Church and its congregation in central Los Santos. Short laps for cars and bikes.
Take down the Fleeca franchise. The driver controls the crowd. The driller gets box 167 from the vault. Then everyone gets out, and gets away in the Kuruma.

I like to know what's happening in the city. Some call it micro-management. I call it staying ahead of trouble. Now, there are some new guys selling too-pure coke all over. I wanna know who they are, and I want them gone. Busting a deal in Rancho would be a good place to start.
You got the truck and the meth lab locations, so we bout ready to get on it. Light up the lost fools labs, grab the product and don't let nobody stop you from gettin that crank tank back. Cool?

Listen, we've got a big problem in the form of a huge asshole. Oh yeah. Some smart guy's running his mouth about his local laundering network. Why don't you show him what happens to folks who think they do business better than us?
Clear out the flagship branch of the Pacific Standard Bank on Vinewood Blvd. Bust into the bank, control the crowd, crack the vault, pull out what you can, and make a getaway on the bikes.

Break Rashkovsky out of Bolingbroke. Ground team takes the transport bus, poses as guard and inmate, and goes into the prison to get him out. Demolitions takes care of the inbound transport bus. Pilot collects them in the plane.

Ok our mans on the inside and your ramp is all set up. Now you got a date with Lil Dee and them targets in Bolingbroke Penitentiary. Get in, clip em, and get Dees fat ass outta there. We bout to hit them rats wit a lil pied piper shit.
It's you and a flimsy piece of material against Nature as you weave down the side of Mount Chiliad from 3425ft.

Tracker placed? Check. Virus? Check. We got everythin we need to pull up on that army convoy and swipe them printing plates. Time to go commando or whatever the hell they be sayin - I dunno that bootcamp shit.
This is it. THIS IS IT. Got everything we need to take the Titan from right under Eberhard's nose. Tell every gun runner in the state, we're about to reopen for business. Woo!

You got the pass and we blackmailed the shit outta that bank manager. Id say its bout time to hit the UD. Throw on that security fit, head into the vault, snatch that gold and as always, keep the getaway wheels rollin, yall.

Follow the party trail as you move from the clubs on Eclipse to the mansions and apartment blocks of Rockford Hills and West Vinewood. Wide boulevards going into narrow drives in this lap race for cars and motorcycles.

Knife edge between buildings and duck under cranes as you fly by Vespucci, Vinewood, and Rockford Hills. If anything goes wrong, you'll kill some construction workers or package tourists, so who cares, right? Lap race in the Vestra business jet.

A jump like this is a true test of focus and mental strength. Don't allow any ideas to creep in about the slapdash packing of you chute or the odds on a faulty ripcord. No don't, really. This 7870ft descent dives sharply, then twists through the Paleto Forest.
The cops have my cousin, El Estupido, surrounded. He's under siege at a farm in Paleto Bay. Two of you get him, and escort him to his chopper at McKenzie Airfield in Grapeseed. You'll be rewarded.

If you're being chased down by fighter jets, you better have something fast to drive. A team of Runners tries to escape from just outside LS International Airport in Coquette sports cars, while Hunters in Lazers come after them. You've only got one life, so make it count as you push for the Alamo Sea. If any of the Runners make it, they win.

A contract goes out to a team of Runners at McKenzie Airfield - can they get some of this hot cargo to LS International? A team of Hunters at Fort Zancudo have been tasked with taking them down in fighter jets. They're playing for keeps - if someone's taken out, they're out for good. Only one runner needs to make it for the run to be a success.

In this team deathmatch, there are Winners and Losers, and success comes at a price. With the winning team visible on the radar, the Losers can sneak their way to the top. And that's the American Dream. First team to the target score wins.

In this team deathmatch, there are Winners and Losers, and success comes at a price. With the winning team visible on the radar, the Losers can sneak their way to the top. And that's the American Dream. First team to reach the target score wins.

In this team deathmatch, there are Winners and Losers, and success comes at a price. With the winning team visible on the radar, the Losers can sneak their way to the top. And that's the American Dream. First team to reach the target score wins.
Sixteen rider motorcycle point to point, corkscrewing down from the hills near the Galileo Observatory to the gates of Fort Zancudo. Road and off road sections.

French bicycle races may have lofty alpine scenery, drugged up manorexics and classical architecture, but when it comes to heavy industry, polluted beachfronts, and real criminal activity there's just nothing like a stage in LS. Classic point to point bicycle race through the detritus of the Del Perro coastline.
A simple race for simple people who want to seem complicated. Lap circuit for muscle cars around Mirror Park with some long straights on the Los Santos Freeway.
No concerns over doping in this contest: 30 possibly meth-addled bikers show those hallucinations who's boss with some short, precise laps around the Grapeseed. Watch out for the bridge.

Get in touch with your inner pioneer on this venture into the wilderness round Sandy Shores, where the great frontier traditions of sunstroke, incest and cannibalism have been so lovingly preserved. Off-road race with plenty of jumps along the dirt roads around Route 68.

Deathmatch in a Grand Senora trailer park. Unspoiled desert living (and dying) if you ignore the transmission towers, utility poles, satellite dishes, wind farm, train line, and maximum security prison in the distance.

With only a few minutes before a shipment of seized goods rolls into the station, you can be sure of one thing: every tax-exempt entrepreneur in the city is on the way, and platform space is at a premium.

At times of near-certain death, you can find yourself facing profound questions. Has your life been little more than an endless round of intoxicated consumption? Is driving a Super car down a mile of vertical tarmac the same as just falling out the sky? Is 2000 feet really the time to switch to a motorbike with a jet engine? Yes to all, by the way. Lap Transform Race starting in Super cars, also featuring the Oppressor and Besra.

Nothing brings out the full elegance of classical architecture better than gasoline spills, tire tracks and smoldering debris. No time to stop and break out the Snapmatic, though. Some asshat is going to drop a flying bike on your head before you can say 'postmodern fusion'. Lap Transform Race starting in Super cars, also featuring the Nokota and Oppressor.

Sure, you can turbo your hyperbike through jumps, rings, and tubes and make it look easy - but can you deal with the Vespucci canals? Rusting strollers, ex-FIB informants, the flaming wreckage of hovercars and amphibious quads - sometimes the naturally occurring obstacles are the trickiest. Lap Transform Race starting on motorcycles, also featuring the Deluxo, Blazer Aqua and Thruster.

In the land of the free and the home of the ruthless, two things are certain; first, you choose your own route; second, barely anyone is coming out of this alive. Lap Transform Race starting on Motorcycles, also featuring the Mallard, Ruiner 2000, Vestra and Blazer Aqua.

Like any proud citizen of Los Santos, you've seen the shopping carts, dead bodies and rusted pickups filling the Land Act Reservoir, and you think it's a disgrace. This city deserves a better class of refuse in its main water supply, and a few crashed muscle cars, vintage motorbikes and stunt planes would go a long way to raising those standards. Time to show you care. Lap Transform Race starting with the Ruiner 2000, also featuring motorcycles, Havok, Blazer Aqua and Mallard.

If you think you've experienced the highs and lows of city center finance in Los Santos, think again. Turns out, there's a certain kind of high you need a tactical fighter to achieve. And there's a certain kind of bowl-shredding low you only get when you drop out of the sky in a ton of Super car. Buckle up. Point to point Transform Race starting in Super cars, also featuring the Mallard and Besra.

The tech only gets better - but can you keep up? Sure, your old sports classic is manageable. You can probably handle a juiced-up stock car, too. But that vicious little hatchback is going to cause trouble - and as for the hypercar... Yeah, you're not ready. Lap Transform Race starting in Sports Classics, also featuring the Hotring, Comet SR, and Tezeract.

Golf in Los Santos is about more than trashing the club house and tipping your caddy with a 9-iron to the knee. Step up to a real sport: your short game might be strong, but how's your drive? Lap Transform Race starting in Super cars, also featuring the Ruiner 2000, Caddy, Rocket Voltic, Cliffhanger, Speeder and Havok.

There are two kinds of people when it comes to achieving and maintaining high speeds in confined environments. There's the surgically precise fighter pilot, and there's the maniac with his foot on the floor of a Phantom Wedge. This time, you're going to need to be both. Lap Transform Race starting in the Molotok, also featuring Motorcycles, Phantom Wedge and Oppressor.

Something about the Los Santos docklands makes for a damn fine shipwreck. But why limit yourself? Super cars, planes and helicopters also make very picturesque seabound detritus. Get creative on this destructive lap Transform Race starting on the Seashark, and also featuring the Shotaro, Super cars, the Mallard and Havok.

You haven't thrown a real San Andreas no-hitter until you've taken five vehicles through the land, sea and airspace of this Blaine County track without crashing, drowning or blacking out even once. Good luck. Lap Transform Race starting in Super cars, also featuring the Vortex, Mallard, Seashark and Havok.

When the apocalypse finally gets underway in San Andreas, and the world lies in ruins, you can bet there will be some interesting racing opportunities in amongst the wreckage. Get practicing for the big day amid the offshore ruins of this lap Transform Race. Starting on Motorcycles, also featuring the Seashark and Mallard.

Even on a good day, Los Santos can be a disorientating place. On a bad day, you're upside down in a closed loop, you can only see the next three feet of track, and you can't remember if you're driving one of the world's fastest cars or a fixed-wing stunt plane. Gotta love the bad days. Lap Transform Race starting in Super cars, also featuring the Mallard.

There's something serene, calming, even naturally majestic about the west coast of San Andreas. If it weren't for the procession of superbikes, fighter jets and amphibious quads doing endless climbs, loops and drops, there'd be nothing to recommend it at all. Lap Transform Race starting on Motorcycles, also featuring the Tyrus, Molotok, Seashark and Blazer Aqua.

Blaine County has so much to offer a sightseer from the big city: hills, valleys, rocky coasts, degenerate rural townships and a world-famous diversity of communicable disease. If you want all the highs and lows with none of the itches and nosebleeds, this track is for you. Point to point Transform Race starting on Motorcycles, also featuring the Besra, Blazer Aqua, Zentorno and Trophy Truck.

If it's your first day in the big city, this is all the orientation you need: watch as the docklands, airport, business district and Legion Square all bleed into a single migraine-inducing blur. Lap Transform Race starting in Super cars, also featuring the Besra, Ramp Buggy and Rocket Voltic.

It's a long way home to the Alamo Sea. Between you and the finish line, you'll have every conceivable chance to fall out of the sky, sink under the waves, or keep things traditional with a roadside fireball. Bonus points for doing all three at once. Point to point Transformation Race starting in Super cars, also featuring the Mallard, Seashark, Havok, Manchez and Ruiner 2000.

It's not paranoia if they really are trying to kill you. Which they are. And it's not tunnel vision if you really are driving and flying through a maze of tunnels, pipes, tubes and all the spaces between them. Which you are. See? There's nothing wrong with you at all. Lap Transform Race starting in Super cars, also featuring the Besra and Oppressor.

Disorientation is a funny thing. You take one too many inverted checkpoints in a fighter jet, and you'd swear you were stuck in a long, winding tunnel dodging rotating fans with absolutely no idea what vehicle you're using. Don't worry, it'll probably clear up soon. Lap Transform Race starting in the Pyro, also featuring Sports Cars, the Avenger and the Rogue.

You might think this is just another fine opportunity to make short work of the stratosphere in a really expensive sports car. And it is - but don't get complacent, because there's a twist or four in the tail of this point to point Transform Race. Starting in Sports cars, also featuring the Besra, Blazer Aqua, Havok, and Akuma.

Split-second decisions can be difficult when you're strapped into the lovechild of a supercar and a space shuttle. And trust us, which turbo-charged loop to take off the start line is just the beginning of this dilemma. Throw in a tightly-wound stunt plane and a herd of pocket-sized helicopters, and your multitasking better be up to scratch. Lap Transform Race starting in the Rocket Voltic, also featuring the Mallard, Havok and Motorcycles.

There's nothing more exhilarating than threading a jetpack between the apartment blocks of downtown Los Santos. There's nothing more arousing than being at the controls of a delta wing military bomber. And there's nothing more psychologically damaging than rapidly moving between the two. Lap Transform Race starting on Motorcycles, also featuring the Thruster, Tezeract and Volatol.

Whether you're weaving through obstacles on two wheels, four wheels or two wings, the fundamental skills are the same: balance, precision, and dodging the flaming wrecks of your former competitors. Lap Transform Race starting on Motorcycles, also featuring the Mallard and XA-21.

There's nothing to touch that moment when you line your shot up perfectly, let the pressure slide right off you, and hit nothing but net. Especially when the guy behind you screws it up by a few feet and his flying muscle car explodes on the rim. Point to point Transform Race starting on Motorcycles, also featuring the Ruiner 2000, Besra, Blazer Aqua, Hauler and Whippet.

Can you survive the Los Santos snake pit? Nope, that's not a euphemism for the dark alley just down the road from Eclipse Towers on a Saturday night. This is the kind of sky-bound snake pit you need a jet trainer and a lot of balls to navigate. Transform Race starting on Motorcycles, also featuring the Buzzard and Besra.

Like all the best pilots in San Andreas, you're used to seeing the Alamo Sea come crashing through your windshield and into your cockpit. Only this time, if you pitch your nosedive just right, you aren't getting wet. Lap Transform Race starting in Off-roaders, also featuring the Seabreeze, Blazer Aqua, Elegy Retro Custom and Ruiner 2000.

What could be more appropriate for a diverse and cosmopolitan city like Los Santos than a race track in honor of the Chinese year of the Giant-Dragon-with-a-Fighter-Jet-in-its-Mouth? Lap Transform Race starting in Compacts, also featuring the Faggio Sport, Molotok and Vagner.

This fiery hurricane of jetpacks, flying cars and vintage classics raging through the heart of Los Santos is brought to you by Grotti, the Italian supercar manufacturer with a low threshold for bad publicity. Even the flaming wreckage is green, white, and red. Lap Transform Race starting in Super Cars, also featuring the Issi Classic, Thruster and Deluxo.

There's only one thing more claustrophobic than driving a fast car between high walls that are actually closing in on you, and that's flying a single-prop fighter between high walls that are actually closing in on you. Take those rapidly confining spaces out to sea, and it's time for that nervous breakdown you've been working on. Lap Transform Race starting in Sports cars, also featuring the Rocket Voltic, Nokota and Blazer Aqua.

It's a rule as old as high-speed racing itself: never fall out of the sky in a rusty tug boat on a full stomach. Or something like that - it doesn't really matter, because you're definitely doing it. Lap Transform Race starting in Super Cars, also featuing the Tug, Blazer Aqua and Dodo.

The few survivors of this track compare it to driving a hypercar up and down the funnel of a tornado in preparation for some technical land, sea and air maneuvers. They also strongly recommend skipping breakfast. Lap Transform Race starting in Super cars, also featuring the Molotok and Dinghy.

There was a time when if you asked any civilized person whether they fancied a high-speed corkscrew hundreds of feet above the Pacific, they would do the decent thing and assume you were hoping to join the mile high club. These days you're not even talking about a plane. Lap Transform Race starting in Super Cars, also featuring the Hydra and Toro.

You know you've made it in Los Santos high society when you can spend the morning cruising under the Vinewood sign, and the afternoon supping cocktails on your antique sailboat off the east coast. And you know you've really made it when you can do both of those things inside a 5 minute lap with an executive chopper and a supercar joining the dots. Lap Transform Race starting on Motorcycles, also featuring the Swift, Marquis, Seabreeze and Vagner.

Last thing you knew, you were joining the solo mile high club in a freefalling Super car above the business district. You blink, and you're piloting a jet fighter straight into a wall. Blink again, and you're not quite sure if this is a rocket-powered Super car or a flimsy ultralight. Either you're on one hell of a come down, or the fun's just getting started. Transform Race starting in Super cars, also featuring the Molotok, Rocket Voltic, Ultralight and Parachutes.

Los Santos isn't Liberty City, but the idiots I'm dealing with still want to be in the waste management business. They think it's a clever front for moving powder. So strange - they must love the smell of trash. Can you stop this stupidity, wipe out the operation, and clean up El Burro Heights for real.

Where the river meets the Ocean meets a lot of iron and concrete - spiraling lap race for Seasharks under the road and rail bridges of South Los Santos. Tight turns and water ramps should make it interesting.
Ride the wall in this motorcycle point to point that loops through the metro tunnels under Los Santos International Airport.

Word has it that the Lost MC are collecting weapons from their supplier at the Ron Alternates Wind Farm. What the real purpose of them turbines is the subject of another missive, it's pertinent right now the Lost don't get them arms and TP Inc. does. When you get 'em, drop 'em at Trevor's trailer, and I'll have some funds for you. R. Jakowski

It's time to hold your ground. Mark as much territory as you can, and try to stop other teams from marking over it. The team with the most turf at the end of a time limit gets a point towards the target total.

It's time to hold your ground. Mark as much territory as you can, and try to stop other teams from marking over it. The team with the most turf at the end of a time limit gets a point towards the target total.
Hug the waterline with this off road point to point starting on Procopio Beach. Up to sixteen racers can follow the North coast down through Paleto State Beach to Paleto Cove.

This dustbowl was once arable farmland supporting dozens of homespun rural communities, which made it terrible for off-roading. Shake off the depression and make the sand dunes work for you on laps of this tight Sanchez race by the Alamo Sea. Remember, we're optimists, so the glass is half full, even when it's half full of dust.
Agent, your next assignment is as follows. Our suspects are relocating their principle assets. You will intercept their convoy and seize the relevant hardware. Be ready for immediate dispatch.

Agent, your final assignment is as follows. You will be granted access to a top-secret agency-controlled site, where you will obliterate all traces of the target software. Do whatever it takes to sanitize the operation. We can't allow any blowback.

Agent, your next assignment is as follows. You will conduct counterintelligence operations against a competing government agency, remaining covert at all times, and eliminating resistance only where necessary. This is a highly sensitive assignment. We require full discretion and no mistakes.

Agent, your next assignment is as follows. A fellow intelligence officer's cover has been compromised. You will find them and exfiltrate them. They are carrying information which is crucial to the success of this investigation.

THIS IS A FEDERALLY CLASSIFIED BRIEF. An undisclosed government agency requires the services of private sector assets to gather intelligence concerning a conspiracy to defraud the American public. The rest of your brief is ears only. If you publish this information, the agency will deny all knowledge.

Okay, this is a hostage rescue operation. To reduce our exposure, we're keeping our extraction force to a minimum. Infiltrating the target building and finding our guy won't be a cake walk. We're grabbing their most valuable asset yet, so fuckups are not an option.

Gravity does most of the hard work when you jump out a chopper from 4000ft. We're going to make it a bit more interesting by staging the drop in the flight path, and making recruits go under a bridge. Best played at night, so you can see the warning lights on obstacles.

Time for night raid training. You're jumping from 4470ft, gliding through a valley on Mount Josiah, and landing inside the military base. Don't forget to pull your legs up going over the fence, or to take your suicide pill if they catch you. Best played at night with a widowmaker chute.

If you've got a pilot's access all areas pass to the blacktop at Los Santos International, well, you gotta make the most of it. High speed lap race for Sports Classics around the possibly-terminal terminal buildings. Look out for baggage carriers, tight turns, and jet engines.
Sure, underpasses can be disconcerting. But this is Vagos turf, so junkies shooting up and getting off are the least of your problems. Buckle up.
Hey hey! You ready to get this thing rolling? Got something real nice and easy to start. Steal from the competition, give to the customer. Think of it as, you know, community support work.
A mid-paced jump from 4100ft into central Los Santos with sweeping, shallow turns so, even if you're screaming like a baby in the air, you'll still look cool and graceful from the ground.
Compact car circuit around scuzzy-chic Downtown Vinewood. Watch out for frat boy tourists and reality TV shoots. Lap race with some tight sections in alleyways.
Dirt bike point to point going along Cassidy Creek and ending at the Alamo Sea. Road section on the Great Ocean Highway and jumps onto, and out of, North Chumash Beach.
Stop the gentrification of Vespucci Beach dead in its tracks with this deathmatch around and on top of the businesses along the beachfront.

If you're looking for all the terrifying excitement of a Los Santos gang war, but you want it classier, more refined, more European - the Vespucci Canals are the destination for you. The most romantic rampage you'll go on today.
Wide streets, sea breeze, steroid junkies, and LS natives showcasing their latest plastic surgery. You'll see it all in this car and motorcycle lap race around 'laid back' West Los Santos.
Isn't it time some minds got blown at Vespucci by something other than medical marijuana? A large, open deathmatch in and around the facilities of Vespucci Beach with little cover.
A Gang Attack at a boatyard to the North of the Alamo Sea.
Show some Vespucci beach bums the true meaning of 'spaced out' with this steep parachute descent from 2980ft. See how many checkpoints you can hit before opening your chute.

Tear up the streets of Vinewood Hills and show the millionaires that they're not as segregated from the riffraff as they thought they were. Last Team Standing with 2 teams. You've only got one life, don't waste it.
Get properly medieval at a castle-like mansion in Richman. It's got turrets, fountains, and pools - make them run with blood in this deathmatch which works best with teams.

Wine tasting tours around San Andreas are liable to end badly - mainly because you're stuck in a car all day, drinking from sun up to sun down, and wine snobs are usually a-holes. Ensure your tour ends really badly with this deathmatch at Marlow Valley Vineyard.

Cutting remarks about the quality of this year's Merlot escalate quickly in this strategic LTS set in the Tongva Hills. Teams begin separated and you can either band together or go it alone, but watch out: wine country is also a sniper's paradise. You've only got one life, get wasted.

Known as the scuzzy-luxury hotel of choice for its cut-price escort services and high profile assassinations, the Von Crastenburg is also an excellent spot for two street gangs to settle their differences. Get up close and personal with your opponents in the cramped alleys behind the hotel, or wrestle control of the center ground in the multi-storey garage. You've only got one life, don't waste it.
If you fall off the corporate ladder, it can be a long, long way down. There are no golden parachutes in this Buzzard deathmatch above the Business district. Watch your six, nine, twelve, and three.

Someone told me, so I'm telling you - the Lost MC about to sell a nice piece of white to some free love types at the Senora Desert Trailer Park. They hippies, but I guess the dudes love yuppie drugs. Who knows. Just bring the product round my spot, and I'll pay you for it.

Anyone who knows me will tell you I'm a firm believer in the US justice system - any system that imprisons the poor, and lets the rich go free is okay by me. Only there's one judge who doesn't understand how this country works. He's at the Marlowe Valley Vineyard. Take him out, and send a message.

I'd normally do this job, but running the operational side of the business, and my radio broadcasts, I don't got time - just so you know. We need you to get a shipment of crystal the Lost have in a boat in Paleto Cove, and take it to our kitchen on Alamo Sea to be cut down. The bikers'll be protecting it - look out! R. Jakowski

Don't let the Alamo Sea sunrise in front of you distract you from what's 4000ft below - the blood and guts of your competitors on the cliffs of Mount Josiah. Only glory-hungry fools attempt to freefall the final ridge run of this merciless jump. You're not interested in glory, right?

Well, boss. You've got one last lesson in the art of seamanship. At the end of the day, it is a captain's duty to always tie up loose ends. And in our case, that may or may not involve submarines, sea mines and an amphibious assault. All in a day's work by now, eh?
You don't need reminding of the importance of harnessing the power of wind when you're crouched by the door of a helicopter at 3280ft, but this jump hammers the point home.
San Andreas at its most scenic, particularly when it's not raining fire. Race boats down the rapids of Raton Canyon in a point to point that takes you from the Ocean to the Alamo Sea.

In the late 80s and early 90s, we thought East Asia would take over the world, starting with some high rise office blocks in West LS. But a decade of economic crisis followed instead. Race like a master of the universe in this short lap circuit around the Wiwang Tower. For cars and bikes.

Using Oppressor bikes, take down a rogue Company Mobile Operations Center at our own HQ. The target will have ground support and be utilizing deceptive techniques. Equipment should be returned on completion of task.

From the feed store to the farmer's market. Fight up and down Grapeseed main street and appreciate this slice of heavily government subsidized Americana. Blaine County deathmatch that works best with teams.

It's theoretically possible to win a round of Wreck It by crossing the line first in a fair-and-square lap race. But don't worry: that's never happened, because the alternative is coasting across the line after you've reduced any serious competition to heaps of smoldering scrap metal. Like the old saying goes, if it's not a race to the death, you're just not taking it seriously enough.

But don't worry: that's never happened, because the alternative is coasting across the line after you've reduced any serious competition to heaps of smoldering scrap metal. Like the old saying goes, if it's not a race to the death, you're just not taking it seriously enough.
A Gang Attack at the abandoned refinery near Zancudo Miltary Base.
Welcome to one square mile of high fences, barbed wire, juiced up marines and heavy ordinance. If you want to make your continued existence something to really boast about, this is your chance.

What are we teaching our children? 'Swag' - you know what that means? All they value are fast cars, and nice shoes, but they will not work hard for it. Take this repossession, a tricked out silver Baller in a low income area. Swagging indeed. It makes me sad but you must collect and bring it back here. Until society changes, we cannot.

One of the few remaining areas of Los Santos where the factory workers aren't hipsters in disguise, Banning also hosts the finest amphibious combat in town. Two teams have come ashore on either side of the naval storage yard: either they fight in amongst the gas holders, or brave the crossing to the SS Bulker on the opposite shore where they can snipe their enemies in comfort. You've only got one life, don't waste it.
One gun. One bullet. One shot. One kill. Take out an enemy to gain another shot or scavenge for extra ammo. First to the target score wins.

Do some inhumane experiments of your own at Humane Labs and Research's high tech facility in the San Chianksi Mountains. Deathmatch at the biolab you might have only seen from the inside. Works best with teams.

Let's face it: although you can get behind the naked aggression and anarchic mob-rule, you've never understood the rules of soccer. Well, Bomb Ball gets rid of all those fussy technicalities and restrictions on violence, and boils things down to the real heart of the matter: shoving enormous explosive devices into the other team's half before they go off. Welcome to the beautiful game.

I need the best for this and that's why I came to you. One of my guys has been arrested. They were holding him in Paleto County but he's being moved out to Bolingbroke Prison on the next bus. Can you intervene and spring the fool? I'll make it worth your while. Bring him back to the warehouse - he can lie low here until the heat eases off. Just make sure the cops don't follow you.

There's no need to overcomplicate things: Americans have always known how to have good, old fashioned, rats-in-a-sack, murder-orgy fun. All we need to do is provide a fresh and unpredictable set of tools, roll the cameras, and get the hell out of the way. No mercy, no disqualification, no safe word.

Eh dog, we got ourselves a problem. The homie Leroy's been snatched like a sucker. You know me, dog, I ain't no mark, I ain't goin' pay and I ain't goin' snitch. But I like the dude, so if you can get him back, I'm a break you off something. I heard the Ballas got him in a van going around the city. A'ight. Look after yourself.

You know me, my friend, I am a philanthropist at heart. Maybe I shouldn't have given credit to a young entrepreneur with all the rumors of his involvement in the drug trade, but I want to see the best in people and support new business. Can you please collect the black Coquette he took, and bring it to the showroom. And try not to scratch it, okay.

Few would argue that the worst two things to ever happen to the Senora Desert are meth and biker gangs. So, by taking out the Lost at their new meth lab, you'll be doing everyone a favor, including yourself. Put a couple of people on the hilltop to provide cover while the others move in, then steal their RVs and drive them to the drop-off point.

Deathmatch that works best with teams at the STD contractors' site in Little Seoul, soon to be La Puerta Apartments. Hardhats are non-essential as you fight in the foundations of this impressive erection by the Del Perro Freeway.

Make a statement about late-Capitalism or income equality or art or pointless statements or something by trashing condos in Puerto Del Sol. Contend style Capture going for the last of the party supplies in a courtyard between two identical apartment blocks.
Lap race around the farms, fields, moonshine stills, and meth labs of rural Blaine County. Flat motorbike track circling Grapeseed with road and off road sections.

Last chance to tear up the gritty, industrial streets of Cypress Flats before the real estate vultures swoop in there and turn all those factories into luxury lofts. Last Team Standing with 2 teams. You've only got one life, don't waste it.

Forget the rollercoaster and the ferris wheel, create your own fun at the Del Perro Pier with the kind of thrill ride that will scare the tourists off for good. Last Team Standing with 2 teams. You've got one life, don't waste it.
Fight your way through Casino security to get to the vault. Gain access to the vault, take everything you can, and fight your way back out with the loot, leaving a trail of destruction behind you.

You know better than anyone how I foster entrepreneurship. Some would call me a mentor. But I have been too trusting, too lenient, and now one of my dealers is meeting with the Vagos, hoping to play us off against each other. I want you to show him the error of his ways. He has family connections, so we need to be careful. Make it look like another gang ran a hit, then disappear.

The LS Tourist Board invites you to explore the natural wonders of the Grand Senora. Discover unique flora blooming in the 100° heat. Come upon inedible fauna clinging to life. Gasp with delight as dragsters smash the Eastern Motel sign. Natural selection is a marvel.

These days, Mirror Park’s considered one of the most desirable neighborhoods in Los Santos and it’s not hard to see why. Where else could you drift sidewise through Horny’s drive thru and grab a quarter pounder on your way to immortality? Lap race for drift vehicles.

Someone's employed Merryweather Security to guard a boat at the Pacific Allied Shipyard. I happen to know the boat is loaded with bricks of cocaine. Find out how these mercenaries got roped into the war against drug control, and bring the boat to my men in the marina. The employment records should be in their safe.
Deathmatch at the Los Santos Marine train yard on Elysian Island. Unpack your aggression in the shadow of the Miriam Turner Overpass.

The foothills of Mount Chiliad are known for their diverse ecosystem, big-bushed naturists and entrenched bands of mercenaries in hillside camps. One team holds the fort, while the other brings the fight to them from three directions: a frontal assault, a risky descent from the hills above, and air support from the handy fleet of attack helicopters parked up on the beach. You've only got one life, don't waste it.

Troops have been mobilised to deal with an outbreak of charitable giving in downtown Los Santos, leaving Fort Zancudo with just a skeleton crew, and you with the opportunity for some opportunistic slaughter on a grand scale. It may be the biggest airbase in the state, but it can still feel claustrophobic with 30 industrious maniacs crawling all over it in search of each others' blood.

Regulation Air Force exercises happen at high altitude over the ocean, but where's the fun when you can't get a feel for how fast you're flying? Lap race for planes over rural Eastern Blaine County. How close to the dirt can you go without taking the head off a fruit picker?

When it comes to brutal arena designs, you can install the most exquisitely hazardous death traps on the market, but there's just no substitute for the sheer ingenuity and sadism of a properly incentivized human being. One team collects checkpoints, the other uses every fiendish tool at the arena's disposal to make their plans go up in smoke. And be sure to hold onto your grudges: after every round, you switch places.
Off road point to point along the north coast of the Alamo Sea. Some of the prettiest scenery in the State. The locals don't see city folk much, so don't let them catch you alone.

One of the many ''government facilities'' in the country. Employees at this anonymous building outside the city listen to your conversations, and read your emails for your own safety. Deathmatch at the NOOSE office that works best with teams.

Not just for parolees and perverts anymore, a fleet of buses at the Dashound Bus Center in Downtown LS becomes a target for two teams of hoods. They compete to get buses back to their bases on either side of the city, while trying to stop the other team from doing the same.

Once upon a time, if you wanted to enjoy a pitched battle on a blazing oil field you had to join the army and go to the Middle East. These days, dedicated amateurs can stage the whole thing without leaving small-town America. Two teams compete to steal tankers of high-grade fuel from the local power station and drive them back to base through a hail of enemy fire. And yes, those first degree burns mean you're doing it right.
It's time to make your move. Infiltrate the compound, grab the goods, and get out in one piece. How you pull the heist off is up to you.
It's time to make your move. Infiltrate the compound, grab the goods, and get out in one piece. How you pull this heist off is up to you.

Say what you like about gladiatorial fights to the death as a form of mass entertainment - they've got no hangups about being fair. One team takes to the arena in monster trucks capable of crushing metal and bone into the same bloody dust. The other guys get compact cars and a dose of anxiety meds - but if even one of them survives, they win. Let the games begin.

It's a dark day in Los Santos when even the hard-won spoils of organised crime are a target for other, less industrious criminals. One crew's objective is simple: get what's wrongfully yours back to base. Their opponents have an ambush set up in the south and a fast-moving team rolling in from the north. Don't get complacent: once a prize is back at your base, it's still fair game for the other side. And if you're expecting the cops to leave you all to it, think again.
Lap race up and down the narrow canyon drives of Richman and Rockford Hills. Compact cars and motorbikes on this figure of eight track. Short off road section, but mainly paved.

What's the last thing an indicted M and A VP sees after exiting the window of his corner office? Today, it's not his recently repossessed Infernus, it's you and 29 other psychopaths doing laps in military grade jets. Technical air race passing between skyscrapers, through cranes, and under bridges. Welcome to the business district.

When a normal person wants to get out of the city, they have to sit in traffic for hours. Business leaders jump a jet and get out in minutes. Point to point for Vestras heading due North. Over the Kortz Center to Great Chaparral, past Mount Josiah, and all the way to Procopio Beach.

The legal system falls apart if jury members are not honest. We approached twelve members of a jury, and paid them to bring down a guilty verdict. My competitor must have paid them more for innocent. Only because they took my money do I greenlight all of them. Take them out quick, or the authorities will catch on.

Alright, now we have Labrat back, it's time to go on the offensive!!! We heard that Friedlander is holed up in a Rehab Center in Richman. That's where he's running trials on his mind-humping party drops based on our recipe. No way are we ever letting that slide. It's fucked. It's perverted. And not in a spicy way. We gotta get up there and put a stop to this.

Your boy LD got word on pharmaceutical exchange happening between the Vagos and the Ballas at a storage depot under the freeway in Strawberry. You get the product, bring it to the boy, Gerald, he will hook you up. Straight.

A'ight, so I got something for you. They some Lost dudes up at the graveyard rabble rousing or whatever they call it. Some of the OGs been wanting 'em gone a while now, and this our chance to get 'em all at once. Go to the spot and take the bikers down, there'll be some snaps in it for you for sure. The OGs ain't got a rep for generosity, but in this case they goin' make an exception.

There's a new iFruit phone about to come out, rumors of another war in the middle east, more starvation in Africa, but here I am, sitting in my trailer, wondering who's gonna do something about the Lost's new crystal factory on the other side of the Alamo Sea!! What? You are? Well, get to it and bring the crank to my yard!!

Alright, fool. I got word on a hustle. It's outside a town at this serious dealer's spot, but you don't gotta deal with him. He's been selling chemicals to some hillbilly types cooking out their RV. Boost the caravan and meet my dudes at the YouTool depot off the freeway. You get money, and I'm in the crystal game. It's all good.

Here’s our guy. Omar Garcia – party boy, douchebag, street racer, car thief. Classic combo in this town. You’re gonna have to be real fast to catch this one, but then I heard you’ve been known to break a few traffic laws yourself.

Carnage comes to the Caribbean as 2-4 teams drop into the tropical paradise-turned-murder zone of Cayo Perico. Commandeer a tank for a ground-offensive, control the skies in a military helicopter, or remain on-foot and off-radar and sit out the massacre completely, hoping you emerge as the last one standing – just don't forget that the arena border is shrinking. Whoever said island life was peaceful?
Question: what's the only situation with a lower life expectancy than an imminent nuclear strike? Answer: sneaking into the missile silo, digging in, screaming HOOAH ASSHOLES, and starting the clock.

You wanna help me get a big shipment of weapons together for a contact of mine to take to Mexico? There's a slight chance they won't be used for something totally horrendous down there too. So we can all feel good about that. Weapons are with the Lost at the cement works in Harmony, buyer's waiting for whole consignment (whole consignment!!) at Catfish View boatyard.
Two teams on death row in Bolingbroke State Penitentiary. Who's walking out of there? Last Team Standing with 2 teams. You've only got one life, don't waste it.

Sticking punks up is the perfect hustle for the new kid in town. Marks ain't gonna recognize you, won't be able to come back. Take advantage of that low profile at a meet under the Del Perro Pier. I don't care what happens to the Lost and Vagos dudes involved, long as the product finds its way to my spot. Oh yeah, there'll be some change in it for you.

The side of the warehouse says no trespassing, no loitering. Splitting into teams and fighting to the death isn't mentioned. Deathmatch that works best with teams amongst the rusted metal and oil derricks in the DEE Oil lot in El Burro Heights.

When you think about it, Los Santos Port is a business incubator for small, motivated gun smuggling and drug trafficking startups from across the globe. Yeah, they fight. Yeah, they raid each other's product. But competition makes the industry stronger, and the Port always wins. Like they say, innovate or die.
Fulfill your childhood dream of competing on the Redwood Lights Motocross Track. Lap race on dirt bikes with multiple jumps.

Predatory pricing is an ugly business, my friend. You take your eye off your competitors for a moment, and they flood the market with imports. Now we must give the law of supply and demand a little assistance, yes? Go to their warehouse and remind them how market competition works in the land of the free. Destroy every last car.

Alright, we're prepping an attack at Davis Quartz. Intel suggests Merryweather's crawling all over the quarry and whatever they're safeguarding down there, we want it. This is high tier, so grab your wings and give them something to cry about.

We all know the FIB listen to our calls, read our emails, LifeInvader alerts, and Bleets, but it turns out they actually get some useful information as well. So useful, I will pay you heavily to get it back off them for me. Ambush the team, and bring their files to my place. You'll be rewarded.
After all that hard work crowd funding the business, it's time to make some money. Come to the warehouse and help move two vans loaded with product.
Use the Deluxos to get close to multiple target vehicles and hack them to recover data packages.
The title says it all. Small-scale deathmatch around the church in Paleto Bay that's locked to shotguns. It'll be a lot less bloody than divorce.

I like beautiful things - modernist houses, Aztec artifacts, impressionist masterpieces. I will pay for them, of course, but sometimes that isn't possible. A painting caught my eye in the Kortz Center museum, but they won't sell it. They're shipping it to an exhibition in Amsterdam. Stop the Merryweather convoy before it gets to the docks, evade the police and bring the crate back to me.

City planning at its finest - negotiate the complex system of freeway interchanges around Los Santos International Airport in this lap race for cars and motorcycles. Then be grateful you're not late for a flight at rush hour or on the way to a concert at the Maze Bank Arena.

The Land Act Dam has been the site of many unsolved murders over the years, including young Vinewood starlet Leonora Johnson in the 1970's, and that tally is about to see a drastic spike. Last Team Standing with 2 teams. You've only got one life, don't waste it.

Normally I don't concern myself with professional thieves. You want to rob a bank, who am I to get in the way? Unless you hit one of my safety deposit boxes, or have something I want, then you have nothing to worry about. There's a crew down at the Port who have something I want, a shipment of arms I can use. Go down there and bring it back to me.

You know how to party in Del Perro. Beat LS's legendary drivers in a breakneck street race, slam some cocktails at Bahama Mamas, blackout on the dancefloor, and wake up spewing cotton candy on Pleasure Pier. Time to initiate phase one. Lap race for Los Santos Tuners.

Left or right? High road or low road? Strike out alone or stick with the pack? This is a track for members of the free world - because if the American dream is about anything, it's about the freedom to make a series of largely meaningless choices while in a bloodthirsty competition with a bunch of strangers. Lap race for motocycles.

Somewhere thousands of feet above the Pacific Ocean, up there with migrating birds and the government-financed chemtrails, there's a nutjob falling out of the sky in a million-dollar supercar. But there's a smile on his face, because he's winning. That nutjob could be you. Believe. Lapped race for supercars.

There's a fine line between an epic descent and falling uncontrollably out of the sky, and which side you're on is going to depend on talent, judgement and just how hard the other guy is trying to kill you. Classic point to point stunt race for super cars.

Who hasn't stood in the heart of Los Santos and looked up, past the tops of the skyscrapers, through the blanket of smog, deep into the rapidly deteriorating ozone and thought ''yes, that's an ideal starting point for a stunt race''? Don't get used to the view - you'll be down again real soon. Point to point stunt race for supercars.

The problem with outstanding natural beauty is that it can distract you from the perfect racing line. And there's nothing like a six-foot wide, hundred-foot tall trench for keeping your focus firmly on the carcinogenic waste belching out of the superbike in front. Point to point stunt race for motorcycles.

It's time to brush off your territorial instincts in this remix of the classic adversary mode. The bottom line is the same: be in the safe zone when the timer runs out - or prepare to overheat, permanently. But this time, as well as getting smaller, the safe zone changes location every time the clock resets, and bits of the track might disappear at random. Stay sharp.

The most action industrial East LS is going to see until it gets redeveloped into retail space, and -loft- apartments for bankers with a creative streak. Deathmatch in the loading bays off Orchardville in Cypress Flats. Works best with teams.

Arena War isn't all about ruthless individualism. Sometimes there really is safety in numbers - and in Tag Team you're going to need it. Each team has one player in the arena at a time, and their only objective is to immolate the opposition. If you're taking heavy fire you can tag in one of your teammates, but remember, this only ends one way - and it's you or them.

Security pass ready, schematics good to go. Guess its time to bust into the IAA, find that dealer, and politely ask his ass to give up where this hotshit formulas at. Gonna be high heat for some piece of paper, but one piece of paper for our client means a whole lotta paper for us, feel me?
Arrive in Los Santos in style with this sweeping descent into the city center from 5419ft, and wave at all the drones in their office cubicles on the way down.

I've had a tap into some of our competitor's phones. They've been getting careless with their burners recently. It seems the architectural plan for a certain well-known financial institution is going to be changing hands at a parking lot in Pillbox Hill. Could you persuade them to part with it? They'll have a lot of heat so probably best to split up your guys. Put some snipers on the roof while the rest go in for the documents. Good luck.

Over the years the government has collected enough information on you to predict your individual bowel movements, so here's something they won't see coming: a lunatic drop from 4000ft, cutting your primary chute in time to freefall between the FIB and IAA towers. There's no algorithm for anticipating that kind of stupid.

I got us another lick - hijacking chemicals, lo. They might be for cooking crank, they might be for dry cleaning, I don't know. What I do know is my buyer's gonna break off something fat when he gets 'em. The tanker is on the way to the Palmer-Taylor power station in Palomino, so just jack that thing and take it to the contact. And, uhh, look out for the LSPD.

From sea to shining sea - appreciate the scuzzy, meth ravaged, recession-beaten beauty of this great nation with a point to point for Sovereign bikes. Starts at the Alamo Sea and ends at the Alamo Sea.

Municipal government in Los Santos is a simple business: when the people in charge can't be bribed or ruined, they can always be evenly redistributed across the committee room. Get involved in the political process with this LTS for two teams around Burton's Townhall: one crew starts holed up inside, the other launches a three-pronged assault. Expect close and long range fighting. You've only got one life, don't waste it.

If you're a bored playboy in search of brief physical pleasure and a major health risk, you now have more than one reason to spend an afternoon down at the Los Santos Docklands. Whether your taste is for sumptuous motorbikes, shapely aquatic quads or illegally imported Russian fighters, there's something to tickle your fancy in this lap Transform Race. Starting on Motorcycles, also featuring the Blazer Aqua, Molotok and the Trophy Truck.

Ever wondered what it would be like to drop a few tabs and race through the title sequence of some vintage 80s sci-fi? Wonder no more with this point to point Transform Race. Starting on Motorcycles, also featuring the Besra and Seashark.

Choices, choices. You've only got a few seconds of hurtling down Mount Chiliad on a BMX to make the age-old decision. Left or Right? With the pack or on your own? Jet-powered super car or gliding motorbike? Luckily for you, this is one of those times when there's no bad call. Lap Transform Race starting on the BMX, also featuring the FMJ, Rocket Voltic, Besra, Oppressor and Parachutes.

When Los Santos narrowly won the ''most congested air space'' award for the 10th year running, they only took into account industrial and commercial traffic. If you add in private hires, blimps, airborne motorbikes and choppers navigating mid-air obstacles courses, there's not a city in the world to touch it. Lap Transform Race starting in Sports cars, also featuring the Havok, Besra, Rocket Voltic, Oppressor and Nokota.
